48	f	2017-01-12 21:45:42.143+00	{"expire_at": null, "slug": "th\\u00e9oden", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "url_path": "/homepage/index-page/th\\u00e9oden/", "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Th\\\\u00e9oden</b>\\\\u00a0is a fictional character in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fantasy\\\\\\">fantasy</a>\\\\u00a0novel,\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>. The King of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Rohan</a>, he appears as a major supporting character in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Two_Towers\\\\\\">The Two Towers</a></i>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Appearances\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Th\\\\u00e9oden is introduced in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Two_Towers\\\\\\">The Two Towers</a></i>, the second volume of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>, as the King of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Rohan</a>. By the time of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">War of the Ring</a>, Th\\\\u00e9oden had grown weak with age, and was largely controlled by his chief advisor\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gr%C3%ADma\\\\\\">Gr\\\\u00edma</a>\\\\u00a0(or\\\\u00a0<i>Wormtongue</i>\\\\u00a0as most others in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riddermark\\\\\\">Riddermark</a>\\\\u00a0called him), who was secretly in the employ of the corrupt wizard\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saruman\\\\\\">Saruman</a>. In\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unfinished_Tales\\\\\\">Unfinished Tales</a></i>, it is implied that the failure of the king's health was \\\\\\"...induced or increased by subtle poisons, administered by Gr\\\\u00edma\\\\\\".<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Th%C3%A9oden#cite_note-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0As Th\\\\u00e9oden sat powerless, Rohan was troubled by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Orcs</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dunlendings\\\\\\">Dunlendings</a>, who operated under the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Will_(philosophy)\\\\\\">will</a>\\\\u00a0of Saruman, ruling from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isengard\\\\\\">Isengard</a>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>When his son\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Th%C3%A9odred\\\\\\">Th\\\\u00e9odred</a>\\\\u00a0was mortally wounded at a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fords_of_Isen#First_Battle_of_the_Fords_of_Isen\\\\\\">battle at the Fords of Isen</a>, Th\\\\u00e9oden's nephew\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89omer\\\\\\">\\\\u00c9omer</a>\\\\u00a0became his heir. However, \\\\u00c9omer was out of favour with Wormtongue, who eventually had him arrested.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>When\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf the White</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>, along with Legolas and Gimli, appeared before him in\\\\u00a0<i>The Two Towers</i>, Th\\\\u00e9oden initially rebuffed the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istari\\\\\\">wizard</a>'s advice to oppose Saruman. When Gandalf revealed Wormtongue for what he was, however, Th\\\\u00e9oden returned to his senses. He restored his nephew, took up his sword\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weapons_of_Middle-earth#Herugrim\\\\\\">Herugrim</a>, and in spite of his age, led the Riders of Rohan into the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Hornburg\\\\\\">Battle of the Hornburg</a>. After this he became known as Th\\\\u00e9oden Ednew, the Renewed.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i>The Return of the King</i>, Th\\\\u00e9oden led the Rohirrim to the aid of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>\\\\u00a0at the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">Battle of the Pelennor Fields</a>. In that battle he routed the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harad\\\\\\">Harad</a>\\\\u00a0cavalry, personally killing their chieftain and banner-bearer in the process. He challenged the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>, the leader of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>, and was mortally wounded when his horse\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snowmane\\\\\\">Snowmane</a>\\\\u00a0fell upon him. He was avenged by his niece\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn\\\\\\">\\\\u00c9owyn</a>\\\\u00a0and the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">hobbit</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc \\\\\\"Merry\\\\\\" Brandybuck</a>, who had ridden to war in secret; together, they destroyed the Witch-king. Before mustering the Rohirrim to ride to Gondor's aid, Th\\\\u00e9oden enlisted Merry into his army, but did not let the hobbit ride into\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">battle at Pelennor</a>. In his last moments, he bid farewell to Merry and appointed \\\\u00c9omer the next king.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Th\\\\u00e9oden's body lay in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minas_Tirith\\\\\\">Minas Tirith</a>\\\\u00a0until it was buried in Rohan after the defeat of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>. He was the last of the Second Line of the kings, judging from direct descent from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eorl_the_Young\\\\\\">Eorl the Young</a>.</p>\\"}]", "first_published_at": null, "show_in_menus": false, "host_place_relationship": [{"host_page": 29, "pk": 7, "place": 16}], "title": "Th\\u00e9oden", "host_interest_relationship": [{"host_page": 29, "host_interests": 1, "pk": 6}], "pk": 29, "content_type": 12, "go_live_at": null, "expired": false, "seo_title": "", "search_description": "", "latest_revision_created_at": null, "depth": 4, "live": true, "image": 20, "owner": 1, "numchild": 0, "locked": false, "host_experience_relationship": [{"host_page": 29, "sort_order": 0, "pk": 16, "experiences": 10}, {"host_page": 29, "sort_order": 1, "pk": 17, "experiences": 21}], "path": "0001000100010006"}	\N	29	1
59	f	2017-01-16 21:37:47.42+00	{"path": "0001000100030008", "expire_at": null, "seo_title": "", "search_description": "", "show_in_menus": false, "image": 15, "depth": 4, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Rivendell is an Elven realm in Middle-earth, a fictional world created by J. R. R. Tolkien. It is an important place in Tolkien's legendarium, and is featured in The Hobbit, The Lord of the Rings, The Silmarillion, and Unfinished Tales. It was established and ruled by Elrond Half-elven in the Second Age of Middle-earth (four or five thousand years before the events of The Lord of the Rings), and was protected by the powers of its lord and his elven ring Vilya.</p><p><br/></p><p>Elrond lived in Rivendell with his family \\\\u2014 his wife Celebr\\\\u00edan (until she departed for Valinor), their sons Elladan and Elrohir, and their daughter Arwen \\\\u2014 as well as a sizeable number of other Elves, both Noldor and Sindar. In addition to the family of Elrond, notable Elves who lived in Rivendell included Glorfindel, Gildor, and Erestor. In some writings, featured in Unfinished Tales, Galadriel and Celeborn also lived in Rivendell for a time before they became rulers of Lothl\\\\u00f3rien.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"embed\\", \\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/t9L8Er_oqAQ\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Etymology\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><i>Rivendell</i>\\\\u00a0is a direct translation or\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calque\\\\\\">calque</a>\\\\u00a0into English of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sindarin\\\\\\">Sindarin</a>\\\\u00a0name\\\\u00a0<b>Imladris</b>, both meaning \\\\\\"deep valley of the cleft\\\\\\". The name Rivendell is formed by two English elements: \\\\\\"riven\\\\\\" (split, cloven) and \\\\\\"dell\\\\\\" (valley), making the whole word purport \\\\\\"deeply cloven valley\\\\\\". Imladris was also rendered \\\\\\"<i>Karningul</i>\\\\\\" in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Westron\\\\\\">Westron</a>, the \\\\\\"Common Tongue\\\\\\" of Middle-Earth represented as English in the text of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings.</i>\\\\u00a0It is also referred to as\\\\u00a0<i>The Last Homely House,</i>\\\\u00a0alluding to the elves' old cities, in Beleriand and Aman, and the wilderness (Rhovanion) that lies east of the Misty Mountains.<br/></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\", \\"value\\": {\\"text\\": \\"Evil things do not come into this valley... We are sitting in a fortress. Outside it is getting dark.\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"Gandalf\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Legacy\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In the period of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Counterculture\\\\\\">counterculture</a>\\\\u00a0in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_World\\\\\\">Western World</a>\\\\u00a0of the 1960s and 1970s, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commune\\\\\\">commune</a>\\\\u00a0called\\\\u00a0<i>Maos Lyst</i>\\\\u00a0(<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mao_Zedong\\\\\\">Mao</a>'s Delight) was founded in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denmark\\\\\\">Denmark</a>\\\\u00a0in 1968, its inhabitants replacing their surnames with\\\\u00a0<i>Kl\\\\u00f8vedal</i>, Danish for Rivendell, inspired by Tolkien's Elven outpost.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell#cite_note-6\\\\\\">[6]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0Several of them later became well-known cultural personalities in the country.</p><p>The Canadian progressive rock band\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rush_(band)\\\\\\">Rush</a>\\\\u00a0memorializes Rivendell in the song \\\\\\"Rivendell\\\\\\" on their second studio album\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fly_by_Night_(album)\\\\\\">Fly By Night</a></i>. The song focuses on the tranquillity and seemingly endless time a weary traveller could find there.</p><p>The Austrian folk band Rivendell takes the material for their lyrics almost entirely from Tolkien's books.</p><p>A Californian manufacturer of bicycles,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell_Bicycle_Works\\\\\\">Rivendell Bicycle Works</a>, also uses the name, inspired by the book and a United States backpacking supply company founded in the 1970s called\\\\u00a0Rivendell Mountain Works. They take many of the names of their bicycle models from Tolkien.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell#cite_note-7\\\\\\">[7]</a></sup></p>\\"}]", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "slug": "rivendell", "pk": 19, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-12T20:16:17.711Z", "owner": 1, "live": true, "content_type": 6, "url_path": "/homepage/place-index-page/rivendell/", "expired": false, "numchild": 0, "go_live_at": null, "locked": false, "title": "Rivendell", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T20:16:17.742Z"}	\N	19	1
