dell\\\\\\" (valley), making the whole word purport \\\\\\"deeply cloven valley\\\\\\". Imladris was also rendered \\\\\\"<i>Karningul</i>\\\\\\" in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Westron\\\\\\">Westron</a>, the \\\\\\"Common Tongue\\\\\\" of Middle-Earth represented as English in the text of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings.</i>\\\\u00a0It is also referred to as\\\\u00a0<i>The Last Homely House,</i>\\\\u00a0alluding to the elves' old cities, in Beleriand and Aman, and the wilderness (Rhovanion) that lies east of the Misty Mountains.<br/></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Legacy\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\", \\"value\\": {\\"text\\": \\"Evil things do not come into this valley... We are sitting in a fortress. Outside it is getting dark.\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"Fellowship of the Ring\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"Gandalf\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In the period of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Counterculture\\\\\\">counterculture</a>\\\\u00a0in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_World\\\\\\">Western World</a>\\\\u00a0of the 1960s and 1970s, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commune\\\\\\">commune</a>\\\\u00a0called\\\\u00a0<i>Maos Lyst</i>\\\\u00a0(<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mao_Zedong\\\\\\">Mao</a>'s Delight) was founded in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denmark\\\\\\">Denmark</a>\\\\u00a0in 1968, its inhabitants replacing their surnames with\\\\u00a0<i>Kl\\\\u00f8vedal</i>, Danish for Rivendell, inspired by Tolkien's Elven outpost.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell#cite_note-6\\\\\\">[6]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0Several of them later became well-known cultural personalities in the country.</p><p>The Canadian progressive rock band\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rush_(band)\\\\\\">Rush</a>\\\\u00a0memorializes Rivendell in the song \\\\\\"Rivendell\\\\\\" on their second studio album\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fly_by_Night_(album)\\\\\\">Fly By Night</a></i>. The song focuses on the tranquillity and seemingly endless time a weary traveller could find there.</p><p>The Austrian folk band Rivendell takes the material for their lyrics almost entirely from Tolkien's books.</p><p>A Californian manufacturer of bicycles,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell_Bicycle_Works\\\\\\">Rivendell Bicycle Works</a>, also uses the name, inspired by the book and a United States backpacking supply company founded in the 1970s called\\\\u00a0Rivendell Mountain Works. They take many of the names of their bicycle models from Tolkien.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell#cite_note-7\\\\\\">[7]</a></sup></p>\\"}]", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "slug": "rivendell", "pk": 19, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-16T21:59:44.484Z", "owner": 1, "live": true, "content_type": 6, "url_path": "/homepage/place-index-page/rivendell/", "expired": false, "numchild": 0, "go_live_at": null, "locked": false, "title": "Rivendell", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T20:16:17.742Z"}	\N	19	1
44	f	2017-01-12 21:15:38.178+00	{"expire_at": null, "slug": "arwen", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "url_path": "/homepage/index-page/arwen/", "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Arwen Und\\\\u00f3miel is a fictional character in J. R. R. Tolkien's legendarium. She appears in his novel, The Lord of the Rings, usually published in three volumes. Arwen is one of the half-elven who lived during the Third Age.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Literature\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Arwen was the youngest child of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celebr%C3%ADan\\\\\\">Celebr\\\\u00edan</a>. Her elder brothers were the twins\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elladan_and_Elrohir\\\\\\">Elladan and Elrohir</a>. Her name\\\\u00a0<i>Ar-wen</i>means 'noble maiden'. She bore the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sobriquet\\\\\\">sobriquet</a>\\\\u00a0\\\\\\"Evenstar\\\\\\" (or Evening Star), as the most beautiful of the last generation of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calaquendi\\\\\\">High Elves</a>\\\\u00a0in Middle-earth.</p><p>As told in \\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Tale_of_Aragorn_and_Arwen\\\\\\">The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen</a>\\\\\\",<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arwen#cite_note-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>\\\\u00a0in his twentieth year met Arwen for the first time in Rivendell, where he lived under Elrond's protection. Arwen, then over 2700 years old, had recently returned to her father's home after living for a while with her grandmother\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lady_Galadriel\\\\\\">Lady Galadriel</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lothl%C3%B3rien\\\\\\">L\\\\u00f3rien</a>. Aragorn fell in love with Arwen at first sight. Some thirty years later, the two were reunited in L\\\\u00f3rien. Arwen reciprocated Aragorn's love, and on the mound of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerin_Amroth\\\\\\">Cerin Amroth</a>\\\\u00a0they committed themselves to marry each other.</p><p>Arwen first appears in the text of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>\\\\u00a0in Rivendell shortly after\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>\\\\u00a0awoke in the House of Elrond. She sat beside her father at the celebratory feast. When the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship of the Ring</a>\\\\u00a0came to Lothl\\\\u00f3rien, Aragorn remembered their earlier meeting and paused in reverence on Cerin Amroth.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Shortly before Aragorn took the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paths_of_the_Dead\\\\\\">Paths of the Dead</a>, he was joined by a group of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D%C3%BAnedain\\\\\\">D\\\\u00fanedain</a>\\\\u00a0from the North, accompanied by Arwen's brothers, Elladan and Elrohir, who brought him as a gift from Arwen: a banner of black cloth. The banner was unfurled at the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">Battle of the Pelennor Fields</a>\\\\u00a0to reveal the emblem of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elendil\\\\\\">Elendil</a>\\\\u00a0figured in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mithril\\\\\\">mithril</a></i>, gems, and gold; this became the first triumphant public announcement of the King's return.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\", \\"value\\": {\\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"Arwen\\", \\"text\\": \\"For I am the daughter of Elrond. I shall not go with him when he departs to the Havens: for mine is the choice of Luthien, and as she so have I chosen, both the sweet and the bitter.\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<br/><p>After the War of the Ring, Aragorn became king of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arnor\\\\\\">Arnor</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>. Arwen arrived at\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minas_Tirith\\\\\\">Minas Tirith</a>, and they were married. She gave Frodo a necklace with a white stone, which would aid him when the darkness of his injuries troubled him.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Arwen is a minor character in\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, but she serves as inspiration and motivation for Aragorn, who must become King of both Arnor and Gondor before Elrond would allow her to marry him.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><i>The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen</i>\\\\u00a0relates that Aragorn and Arwen had a son,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eldarion\\\\\\">Eldarion</a>, and at least two unnamed daughters. In\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fourth_Age\\\\\\">F.A.</a>\\\\u00a0121, one year after Aragorn's death, Arwen gave up her life, at the age of 2,901, at\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerin_Amroth\\\\\\">Cerin Amroth</a>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"embed\\", \\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/N4I7myAG_mY\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Background\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Through her father, Elrond, Arwen was the granddaughter of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E%C3%A4rendil\\\\\\">E\\\\u00e4rendil</a>\\\\u00a0the Mariner (the second of the Half-elven), great-granddaughter of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuor\\\\\\">Tuor</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondolin\\\\\\">Gondolin</a>, and therefore a direct descendant of the ancient\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_of_Hador\\\\\\">House of Hador</a>. Through her great-grandmother,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idril\\\\\\">Idril</a>, Arwen was also a descendant of King\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turgon\\\\\\">Turgon</a>\\\\u00a0of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noldor\\\\\\">Noldor</a>. Through her mother, she was the granddaughter of Lady\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>\\\\u00a0and the great-granddaughter of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finarfin\\\\\\">Finarfin</a>.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89omer\\\\\\">\\\\u00c9omer</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Rohan</a>\\\\u00a0said that the Lady Arwen was more fair than the Lady Galadriel of L\\\\u00f3rien, but\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimli_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Gimli son of Gl\\\\u00f3in</a>\\\\u00a0thought differently. Through both of her parents Arwen was a direct descendant of the ancient Elven\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_of_Finw%C3%AB\\\\\\">House of Finw\\\\u00eb</a>. Furthermore, Arwen was a descendant of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beren\\\\\\">Beren</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L%C3%BAthien\\\\\\">L\\\\u00fathien Tin\\\\u00faviel</a>, whose\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Tale_of_Beren_and_L%C3%BAthien\\\\\\">story</a>\\\\u00a0resembled hers. Indeed, Arwen was held to be the reappearance in likeness of her ancestress L\\\\u00fathien, fairest of all the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elves_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elves</a>, who was called Nightingale (Tin\\\\u00faviel). Arwen was one of only three of the Eldar to wed a Man and was descended from the other two, Idril and L\\\\u00fathien.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Arwen was a very distant relative of her husband Aragorn. Aragorn's ancestor,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elros\\\\\\">Elros Tar-Minyatur</a>, the first\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kings_of_N%C3%BAmenor\\\\\\">King</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmenor\\\\\\">N\\\\u00famenor</a>, was her father Elrond's brother, who chose to live as a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Man</a>\\\\u00a0rather than as one of the Eldar. Arwen eventually became Queen of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reunited_Kingdom\\\\\\">Reunited Kingdom</a>\\\\u00a0of Arnor and Gondor when she married Aragorn, who was of the line of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kings_of_Arnor\\\\\\">Kings of Arnor</a>. By Arwen and Aragorn's marriage, the long-sundered lines of the Half-elven were joined. Their union also served to unite and preserve the bloodlines of the Three Kings of the High Elves (<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ingw%C3%AB\\\\\\">Ingw\\\\u00eb</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finw%C3%AB\\\\\\">Finw\\\\u00eb</a>, and the brothers\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olw%C3%AB\\\\\\">Olw\\\\u00eb</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elw%C3%AB\\\\\\">Elw\\\\u00eb</a>) as well as the only line with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maia_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Maiarin</a>\\\\u00a0blood through Arwen's great-great-great grandmother,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melian\\\\\\">Melian</a>, Queen of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doriath\\\\\\">Doriath</a>, and also on Aragorn's side, through the line of kings of Arnor and N\\\\u00famenor to Elros, Elrond's brother, whose great-great-grandmother was also Melian.</p>\\"}]", "first_published_at": "2017-01-09T10:35:32.077Z", "show_in_menus": false, "host_place_relationship": [{"host_page": 11, "pk": 2, "place": 19}], "title": "Arwen", "host_interest_relationship": [{"host_page": 11, "host_interests": 2, "pk": 2}], "pk": 11, "content_type": 12, "go_live_at": null, "expired": false, "seo_title": "", "search_description": "", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-12T21:12:08.466Z", "depth": 4, "live": true, "image": 3, "owner": 1, "numchild": 0, "locked": false, "host_experience_relationship": [{"host_page": 11, "sort_order": 0, "pk": 2, "experiences": 10}, {"host_page": 11, "sort_order": 1, "pk": 5, "experiences": 21}, {"host_page": 11, "sort_order": 2, "pk": 6, "experiences": 20}], "path": "0001000100010002"}	\N	11	1
