p><p>The Canadian progressive rock band\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rush_(band)\\\\\\">Rush</a>\\\\u00a0memorializes Rivendell in the song \\\\\\"Rivendell\\\\\\" on their second studio album\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fly_by_Night_(album)\\\\\\">Fly By Night</a></i>. The song focuses on the tranquillity and seemingly endless time a weary traveller could find there.</p><p>The Austrian folk band Rivendell takes the material for their lyrics almost entirely from Tolkien's books.</p><p>A Californian manufacturer of bicycles,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell_Bicycle_Works\\\\\\">Rivendell Bicycle Works</a>, also uses the name, inspired by the book and a United States backpacking supply company founded in the 1970s called\\\\u00a0Rivendell Mountain Works. They take many of the names of their bicycle models from Tolkien.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell#cite_note-7\\\\\\">[7]</a></sup></p>\\"}]", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "slug": "rivendell", "pk": 19, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-16T22:05:40.244Z", "owner": 1, "live": true, "content_type": 6, "url_path": "/homepage/place-index-page/rivendell/", "expired": false, "numchild": 0, "go_live_at": null, "locked": false, "title": "Rivendell", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T20:16:17.742Z"}	\N	19	1
50	f	2017-01-12 21:54:06.997+00	{"expire_at": null, "slug": "meriadoc-brandybuck", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "url_path": "/homepage/index-page/meriadoc-brandybuck/", "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Meriadoc Brandybuck</b>, usually referred to as\\\\u00a0<b>Merry</b>, is a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fictional_character\\\\\\">fictional character</a>\\\\u00a0from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legendarium\\\\\\">legendarium</a>, featured throughout his most famous work,\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>A lover of boats and maps, Merry is described as one of the closest friends of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>, the main protagonist. Merry is a member of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship of the Ring</a>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Family and relations\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Frodo and Merry are\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cousin#First_cousins\\\\\\">first cousins once removed</a>. Their common ancestors are\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#G\\\\\\">Gorbadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#M\\\\\\">Mirabella Took Brandybuck</a>.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck#cite_note-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Merry was born\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a02982 (or, in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth_calendar#Shire_calendar\\\\\\">Shire-reckoning</a>, in 1382), in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Buckland</a>.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0He is the only child of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#S\\\\\\">Saradoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0(T.A. 2940-<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fourth_Age\\\\\\">F.A.</a>\\\\u00a011), who was a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandybuck_Clan#Masters_of_Buckland\\\\\\">Master of Buckland</a>, and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#E\\\\\\">Esmeralda Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0(n\\\\u00e9e Took) (T.A. 2936-\\\\u00a0?), the younger sister of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#P\\\\\\">Paladin Took II</a>\\\\u00a0(T.A. 2933\\\\u20133034), making him first cousin to Paladin's son\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>. (See\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, Appendix C.)</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Merry later married\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#E\\\\\\">Estella (Bolger) Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0(T.A. 2985\\\\u2013?), the younger sister of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fredegar_Bolger\\\\\\">Fredegar Bolger</a>, who helped Frodo, Sam, Merry and Pippin on the first leg of their quest journey. Meriadoc and Estella had at least one son.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck#cite_note-M-E_Encyc-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Literature\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, Merry is often considered, and was described by Tolkien as, the most perceptive and intelligent of the hobbits. Even before\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins\\\\\\">Bilbo Baggins</a>\\\\u00a0left\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>, he knew of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0and its power of invisibility. He guarded\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>\\\\u00a0after Bilbo's party, protecting Frodo from the various and often unwanted guests. He is knowledgeable and has an innocent, teasing sense of humour. In one incident,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lobelia_Sackville-Baggins\\\\\\">Lobelia Sackville-Baggins</a>\\\\u00a0accused Frodo of being a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandybuck_clan\\\\\\">Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and no true\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_hobbit_families#B\\\\\\">Baggins</a>. Merry assured Frodo, \\\\\\"It was a compliment; and so, of course, not true\\\\\\".</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Merry was also a force behind \\\\\\"the Conspiracy\\\\\\" of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Sam</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Pippin</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fredegar_Bolger\\\\\\">Fredegar Bolger</a>\\\\u00a0and himself to help Frodo. Thus, at the beginning of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">The Fellowship of the Ring</a></i>, Merry was well-prepared and organized \\\\u2014 he assembled their packs and brought ponies. His shortcut through the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Forest\\\\\\">Old Forest</a>\\\\u00a0distanced them from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>\\\\u00a0for a time, though they had to be rescued from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Man_Willow\\\\\\">Old Man Willow</a>\\\\u00a0by the enigmatic\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Bombadil\\\\\\">Tom Bombadil</a>. In the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow-downs_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Barrow-downs</a>, he acquired his sword, which was actually a dagger forged in the kingdom of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arnor\\\\\\">Arnor</a>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>At\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bree_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Bree</a>, Merry was actually not present in the\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prancing_Pony\\\\\\">Prancing Pony</a></i>\\\\u00a0when Frodo put on the Ring; instead, he was outside taking a walk, and was nearly overcome by a Nazg\\\\u00fbl. At\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, he was seen studying maps and plotting their path. He was admitted to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship</a>\\\\u00a0only a little less reluctantly than Pippin; they were the two youngest members, and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>\\\\u00a0had planned on sending them back to the Shire.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"embed\\", \\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/kTnQeasvbZo\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>At the entrance to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moria_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Moria</a>, he asked\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0the meaning of the door inscription \\\\\\"Speak, friend, and enter\\\\\\". When Gandalf discovered the true interpretation, he said, \\\\\\"Merry, of all hosts, was on the right track\\\\\\".</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>At\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amon_Hen\\\\\\">Amon Hen</a>, he was captured, along with Pippin, by a band of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saruman\\\\\\">Saruman</a>'s\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uruk-hai\\\\\\">Uruk-hai</a>, although he gave a good account of himself and was valiantly defended by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boromir\\\\\\">Boromir</a>. Escaping with Pippin into\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fangorn\\\\\\">Fangorn</a>forest, Merry was rescued by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard\\\\\\">Treebeard</a>. Along with Pippin, he drank significant amounts of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ent-draught\\\\\\">Ent-draught</a>\\\\u00a0and grew taller, despite being a fully grown adult Hobbit. Accompanying Treebeard to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entmoot\\\\\\">Entmoot</a>\\\\u00a0and later to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isengard\\\\\\">Isengard</a>, he and Pippin took up residence in an Isengard gate-house. It was here that he first encountered\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Th%C3%A9oden\\\\\\">King Th\\\\u00e9oden</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Rohan</a>, and was reunited with four of the remaining members of the Fellowship.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Merry was separated from Pippin after his friend beheld\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>\\\\u00a0in the\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palant%C3%ADr\\\\\\">palant\\\\u00edr</a></i>\\\\u00a0and was then hastily taken to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>\\\\u00a0with Gandalf on\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shadowfax_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Shadowfax</a>. Merry swore fealty to Th\\\\u00e9oden and became esquire to the king. Against Th\\\\u00e9oden's orders, he rode to Gondor with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn\\\\\\">\\\\u00c9owyn</a>, who was disguised as a common soldier. In the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">Battle of the Pelennor Fields</a>, while the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>\\\\u00a0was preoccupied with \\\\u00c9owyn, Merry stabbed him in the sinew behind his knee with a sword that was made by the D\\\\u00fanedain of Arnor for combat against the Nazg\\\\u00fbl. The Black Captain stumbled from Merry's stroke, and \\\\u00c9owyn seized the moment to strike the Captain's head, destroying him. This fulfilled the prophecy, as he was not killed \\\\\\"by the hand of man,\\\\\\" but rather by a hobbit and a woman. Merry heard Th\\\\u00e9oden's last words, but went unnoticed by the honour escort of Riders; Pippin found him wandering in the city.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>\\\\u00a0healed him and he recovered fully, more quickly than \\\\u00c9owyn.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>For his bravery in battle, Merry was knighted by King\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89omer\\\\\\">\\\\u00c9omer</a>\\\\u00a0as a Knight of the Mark. During the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scouring_of_the_Shire\\\\\\">scouring of the Shire</a>, he led the hobbits in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Bywater\\\\\\">Battle of Bywater</a>, and personally killed the leader of the opposing forces.</p>\\"}]", "first_published_at": null, "show_in_menus": false, "host_place_relationship": [{"host_page": 31, "pk": 9, "place": 17}], "title": "Meriadoc Brandybuck", "host_interest_relationship": [{"host_page": 31, "host_interests": 4, "pk": 8}], "pk": 31, "content_type": 12, "go_live_at": null, "expired": false, "seo_title": "", "search_description": "", "latest_revision_created_at": null, "depth": 4, "live": true, "image": 22, "owner": 1, "numchild": 0, "locked": false, "host_experience_relationship": [{"host_page": 31, "sort_order": 0, "pk": 21, "experiences": 21}, {"host_page": 31, "sort_order": 1, "pk": 22, "experiences": 25}, {"host_page": 31, "sort_order": 2, "pk": 23, "experiences": 23}, {"host_page": 31, "sort_order": 3, "pk": 24, "experiences": 20}], "path": "0001000100010008"}	\N	31	1
