79	f	2017-01-23 07:18:15.996+00	{"host_place_relationship": [{"place": 17, "host_page": 34, "pk": 12}], "pk": 34, "url_path": "/homepage/index-page/pergrin-took/", "go_live_at": null, "live": true, "content_type": 12, "numchild": 0, "expired": false, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Peregrin Took</b>, more commonly known as\\\\u00a0<b>Pippin</b>, is a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fictional_character\\\\\\">fictional character</a>\\\\u00a0from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s fantasy novel\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>. Pippin is introduced as a young\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">Hobbit</a>, and plays a major role as one of the companions of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>, in his quest to destroy the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>. Pippin is a member of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship of the Ring</a>.</p><p></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Overview\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Peregrin was the only son and heir of Paladin Took II, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thain_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Thain</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>. His best friend\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>, more commonly known as Merry, was his cousin; another good friend was\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>'Peregrin' means 'traveller in strange countries'.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took#cite_note-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0Pippin indeed saw much more of Middle-earth than most Hobbits: he journeyed with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo\\\\\\">Frodo</a>\\\\u00a0and the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship of the Ring</a>, and fought in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">War of the Ring</a>. Late in life he travelled again to the kingdoms of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Rohan</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Pippin's hair colour is mentioned as \\\\\\"almost golden\\\\\\" in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_History_of_Middle-earth\\\\\\">The History of Middle-earth</a></i>, vol. IX,\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron_Defeated\\\\\\">Sauron Defeated</a></i>, through the eyes of Pippin Gamgee.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took#cite_note-SD_-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0In the later drafts of this same section Tolkien omitted this statement, leaving the reader to envisage Pippin's appearance.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"The Great Years\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Pippin was the youngest of the four Hobbits who set out from the Shire and the only one who had not yet reached his 'coming of age' at age 33. He was therefore said to be still in his 'tweens' (twenties). He was 28 at the time, while Merry, the next youngest, was 36. At\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>\\\\u00a0almost denied Pippin the chance to accompany Frodo, intending to send Pippin and Merry as messengers back to the Shire.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>, however, supported his and Merry's claims of friendship and loyalty, and the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Elrond\\\\\\">Council of Elrond</a>\\\\u00a0ultimately chose them as the last two members of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship</a>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"embed\\", \\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/5cZ4ABUo6TU\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>After remaining with the Fellowship until its breaking at\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amon_Hen\\\\\\">Amon Hen</a>, Pippin was captured along with Merry by an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Orc</a>-band, which included some of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saruman\\\\\\">Saruman</a>'s\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uruk-hai\\\\\\">Uruk-hai</a>. While held captive by the Orcs, he purposefully dropped his elven brooch (a gift from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lothl%C3%B3rien\\\\\\">L\\\\u00f3rien</a>) as a sign for\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legolas\\\\\\">Legolas</a>, and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimli_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Gimli</a>, who were in pursuit. During a skirmish among his captors, Pippin managed to cut his bonds using a sword held fast by a dead Uruk. In\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Rohan</a>, Pippin and Merry managed to escape when the Orcs were attacked by a company of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)#hosts\\\\\\">Rohirrim</a>, the local hosts. Upon their escape, he and Merry befriended\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard\\\\\\">Treebeard</a>, leader of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ent\\\\\\">Ents</a>. They roused the other Ents to fight against Saruman, and they attacked his stronghold of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isengard\\\\\\">Isengard</a>, partially crippling his power. Due to a special \\\\\\"Ent-draught\\\\\\" that Treebeard made him and Merry drink, Pippin and his cousin became the tallest Hobbits in history, at four and a half feet, surpassing Pippin's ancestor,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bullroarer_Took#Bandobras\\\\\\">Bullroarer Took</a>, who was four feet and five inches tall.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Pippin picked up the\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palant%C3%ADr\\\\\\">palant\\\\u00edr</a></i>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthanc\\\\\\">Orthanc</a>\\\\u00a0after\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gr%C3%ADma_Wormtongue\\\\\\">Gr\\\\u00edma Wormtongue</a>\\\\u00a0threw it at them. Later, obsessed by the mysterious stone, Pippin took it out of Gandalf's hands while the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istari\\\\\\">wizard</a>\\\\u00a0slept, putting a rock in its place. Looking into the stone, he had a terrifying encounter with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>\\\\u00a0himself. In fact, Pippin is the only character in the book who is shown to speak directly to Sauron. To keep Pippin safe from Sauron's forces, Gandalf brought him to the city of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minas_Tirith\\\\\\">Minas Tirith</a>, separating him from his friends.</p>\\"}]", "path": "000100010001000B", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-12T22:07:10.276Z", 