 of Isen; Th\\\\u00e9oden's son, Th\\\\u00e9odred was killed during these attacks) and defeat at the Battle of the Hornburg, where the Huorns came to the aid of the Rohirrim.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>On the heels of this victory, Th\\\\u00e9oden rode with an army to Minas Tirith and helped break its siege in the Battle of the Pelennor Fields, where he was slain. \\\\u00c9omer, the nephew of King Th\\\\u00e9oden, then took up the reign, beginning the third line. Also in this battle, \\\\u00c9owyn, niece of King Th\\\\u00e9oden and sister of \\\\u00c9omer, slew the Lord of the Nazg\\\\u00fbl. \\\\u00c9omer rode with the armies of Gondor to the Black Gate of Mordor and took part in the Battle of the Morannon against the forces of Sauron, who were defeated when the Ruling Ring was destroyed.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The rule of the Stewards of Gondor was then over. King \\\\u00c9omer and the new king of Gondor, Elessar, renewed their oath of alliance, and reaffirmed Cirion's grant of Calenardhon to the Rohirrim. At this time, \\\\u00c9owyn married Faramir, Prince of Ithilien and Steward of Gondor, thus joining the lines of Gondor and Rohan.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In the Fourth Age, Rohan remained in peaceful coexistence with the Reunited Kingdom. A Dwarven community developed in the caves of Helm's Deep, which became prosperous from its mining of precious materials.<br/></p>\\"}]", "path": "0001000100030005", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-23T07:41:15.491Z", "image": 12, "title": "Edoras", "show_in_menus": false, "locked": false, "expire_at": null, "seo_title": "", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T20:00:16.547Z", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "depth": 4, "owner": 1, "slug": "edoras", "search_description": ""}	\N	16	1
