125	f	2017-04-26 03:08:53.058+00	{"depth": 4, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Bilbo Baggins</b>\\\\u00a0is the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Title_character\\\\\\">title character</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protagonist\\\\\\">protagonist</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s 1937 novel\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>, as well as a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supporting_character\\\\\\">supporting character</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>. In Tolkien's narrative\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conceit\\\\\\">conceit</a>, in which all the writings of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>\\\\u00a0are translations from the fictitious volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Book_of_Westmarch\\\\\\">Red Book of Westmarch</a></i>, Bilbo is the author of\\\\u00a0<i>The Hobbit</i>\\\\u00a0and translator of various \\\\\\"works from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_language\\\\\\">elvish</a>\\\\\\" (as mentioned in the end of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>).</p><p></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Hobbit\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"image\\", \\"value\\": {\\"caption\\": \\"Bilbo Baggins illustration\\", \\"style\\": \\"half\\", \\"image\\": 28}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i>The Hobbit</i>, Bilbo Baggins, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">hobbit</a>\\\\u00a0in comfortable middle age at 50 years old, was hired despite his objections as a \\\\\\"burglar\\\\\\" by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istari\\\\\\">wizard</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_The_Hobbit_characters#Thorin.27s_company\\\\\\">13 Dwarves</a>\\\\u00a0led by their king\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thorin_Oakenshield\\\\\\">Thorin Oakenshield</a>\\\\u00a0on a quest to reclaim the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lonely_Mountain\\\\\\">Lonely Mountain</a>\\\\u00a0and its treasure from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragon_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">dragon</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smaug\\\\\\">Smaug</a>. The adventure took Bilbo and the companions through the wilderness, to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">elf</a>\\\\u00a0haven of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, across the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>\\\\u00a0and the black forest of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>, to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esgaroth\\\\\\">Lake-town</a>\\\\u00a0in the middle of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Lake_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Long Lake</a>, and eventually to the Mountain itself. Here, after the dragon was killed and the Mountain was reclaimed, soon after that the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Five_Armies\\\\\\">Battle of Five Armies</a>\\\\u00a0took place.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In his journey, Bilbo encountered other fantastic creatures, including\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Troll_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">trolls</a>, elves,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_animals#Great_Spiders\\\\\\">giant spiders</a>, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beorn\\\\\\">man who can change shape into a bear</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">goblins</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eagle_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">eagles</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warg\\\\\\">wolves</a>\\\\u00a0and a slimy, murderous creature named\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gollum\\\\\\">Gollum</a>. Underground, near Gollum's lair, Bilbo accidentally found a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">magic ring of invisibility</a>, which he used to escape from Gollum.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>By the end of the journey, Bilbo had become wiser and more confident, having saved the day in many precarious situations. Bilbo's journey has been compared to a pilgrimage of grace. The Hobbit can be characterized as a \\\\\\"Christian\\\\u00a0<i>bildungsroman</i>\\\\u00a0which equates progress to wisdom gained in the form of a rite of passage.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0He rescued the dwarves from giant spiders with the magic ring and a short\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_weapons_and_armour#Sting\\\\\\">Elven-sword</a>\\\\u00a0he acquired. He used the ring to sneak around in dangerous places, as well as his wits to smuggle the dwarves out of the elves' prisons. When tensions arose over ownership of the recovered treasure, he tried unsuccessfully to bring the opposing sides to compromise, using the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Arkenstone\\\\\\">Arkenstone</a>, a stolen heirloom jewel, as leverage. This strained his relationship with Thorin, but the two were reconciled at Thorin's deathbed. At the end of the story, Bilbo returned to his home in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0only to find that several of his relatives, believing him to be dead, were trying to claim his home and possessions. In addition to becoming wealthy from his share of the dwarves' treasure, he found that he, like\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adam\\\\\\">Adam</a>, had traded respectability for experience and wisdom. At the end, Gandalf proclaims Bilbo is no longer the Hobbit he was. This is certainly true as Bilbo has fully matured. Continuing the pilgrimage theme, a true pilgrimage does not end at the destination, but rather when the wanderer is absolved, blessed, and ready to return home.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Lord of the Rings\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">The Fellowship of the Ring</a></i>, the first volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, begins with Bilbo's \\\\\\"eleventy-first\\\\\\" (111th) birthday, 60 years after the beginning of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. The main character of the novel is\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>, Bilbo's cousin,<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[nb 1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0who celebrates his 33rd birthday and legally comes of age on the same day.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a02989 (<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_Reckoning\\\\\\">S.R.</a>\\\\u00a01389), Bilbo, a lifelong bachelor, adopted Frodo, the orphaned son of his first cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primula_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Primula Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and his second cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drogo_Baggins\\\\\\">Drogo Baggins</a>, and made him his heir. Though Frodo was actually \\\\\\"his first\\\\u00a0<i>and</i>\\\\u00a0second\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cousin#Cousin_chart\\\\\\">cousin once removed</a>\\\\u00a0either way\\\\\\",<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0the two regarded each other as uncle and nephew.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>All this time Bilbo had kept his magic ring, with no idea of its significance, using it mostly to hide from his obnoxious cousins, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sackville-Baggins\\\\\\">Sackville-Bagginses</a>, when they came to visit.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>'s investigations revealed it to be the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0forged by the Dark Lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>. The Ring had prolonged Bilbo's life beyond the normal hobbit span, and at 111 he still looked 50. While the Ring did not initially corrupt him as it had its previous owners, it was beginning to affect him; over the years, it had begun to prey on his mind when out of his sight, and he lost sleep and felt \\\\\\"thin, sort of\\\\u00a0<i>stretched</i>\\\\u00a0\\\\u2026 like butter that has been scraped over too much bread\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>On the night of his and Frodo's birthday, Bilbo threw himself a party and invited all of the Shire. He signed his home,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>, and estate over to Frodo. He then gave a farewell address to his neighbors, at the end of which he put on the Ring and vanished from sight. As Bilbo prepared finally to leave the house, he reacted with panic and suspicion when Gandalf tried to persuade him to leave the Ring with Frodo. Bilbo refused to give up the Ring, referring to it as his \\\\\\"precious\\\\\\" \\\\u2013 just as Gollum had. Gandalf lost his temper with his old friend and talked some sense into him. Bilbo admitted he would have liked to be rid of the Ring, and he left it behind, becoming the first person to do so voluntarily. He left the Shire that night, and was never seen in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbiton\\\\\\">Hobbiton</a>\\\\u00a0again.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>His earlier adventure, his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eccentric_(behavior)\\\\\\">eccentric</a>\\\\u00a0habits as a hobbit, and his sudden disappearance led to the enduring figure of \\\\\\"Mad Baggins\\\\\\" in hobbit folklore, who disappeared with a flash and a bang and returned with gold and jewels.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Freed of the Ring's power over his senses, Bilbo travelled first to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, and then on to visit the dwarves of the Lonely Mountain. After he returned to Rivendell he spent much of the next 17 years living a pleasant life of retirement: eating, sleeping, writing poetry, and working on his memoirs,\\\\u00a0<i>There and Back Again</i>, known as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. He became a scholar of Elven lore, leaving behind the\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_languages_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elvish</a></i>, which forms the basis of what is known to us as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Silmarillion\\\\\\">The Silmarillion</a></i>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>When Frodo and his friends\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Samwise Gamgee</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>\\\\u00a0stopped in Rivendell on their quest to destroy the Ring, Bilbo was still alive but now visibly aged, the years having caught up with him after he surrendered the Ring. Upon seeing the Ring again, he suddenly tried to take it from Frodo; he returned to his senses when a terrified Frodo backed away, and he broke down in tears, apologizing for bringing the burden of the Ring onto Frodo.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>After the quest to destroy the Ring was fulfilled in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>, Gandalf and the four Hobbits visited Rivendell on their way back to the Shire and found Bilbo still living there. He gave Frodo a set of manuscripts that later became\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the Elvish</i>, and also gave Sam a small bag of gold that represented the last of his share from Smaug's vast hoard. Two years later Bilbo accompanied Gandalf,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>, and Frodo to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grey_Havens\\\\\\">Grey Havens</a>, there to take ship for\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tol_Eress%C3%ABa\\\\\\">Tol Eress\\\\u00eba</a>\\\\u00a0across the sea, on 29th 'September'\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a03021. He had already celebrated his 131st birthday by this time, surpassing the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Took\\\\\\">Old Took</a>\\\\u00a0by one year and becoming the oldest Hobbit ever in Middle-earth. (The natural lifespan of Hobbits is about 100 years.)<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-4\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\"}]", "title": "Bilbo", "host_experience_relationship": [{"pk": 41, "experiences": 10, "sort_order": 0, "host_page": 38}, {"pk": 42, "experiences": 23, "sort_order": 1, "host_page": 38}], "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:23:37.638Z", "host_place_relationship": [{"pk": 16, "place": 18, "host_page": 38}], "numchild": 0, "search_description": "", "locked": false, "path": "000100010001000F", "host_interest_relationship": [{"pk": null, "host_interests": 11, "host_page": 38}], "pk": 38, "go_live_at": null, "slug": "bilbo", "owner": 1, "show_in_menus": false, "expire_at": null, "live": true, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-23T07:42:47.149Z", "url_path": "/homepage/index-page/bilbo/", "content_type": 12, "image": 27, "seo_title": "", "expired": false}	\N	38	1
126	f	2017-04-26 03:09:25.133+00	{"depth": 4, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Bilbo Baggins</b>\\\\u00a0is the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Title_character\\\\\\">title character</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protagonist\\\\\\">protagonist</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s 1937 novel\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>, as well as a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supporting_character\\\\\\">supporting character</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>. In Tolkien's narrative\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conceit\\\\\\">conceit</a>, in which all the writings of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>\\\\u00a0are translations from the fictitious volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Book_of_Westmarch\\\\\\">Red Book of Westmarch</a></i>, Bilbo is the author of\\\\u00a0<i>The Hobbit</i>\\\\u00a0and translator of various \\\\\\"works from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_language\\\\\\">elvish</a>\\\\\\" (as mentioned in the end of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>).</p><p></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Hobbit\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"image\\", \\"value\\": {\\"caption\\": \\"Bilbo Baggins illustration\\", \\"style\\": \\"half\\", \\"image\\": 28}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i>The Hobbit</i>, Bilbo Baggins, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">hobbit</a>\\\\u00a0in comfortable middle age at 50 years old, was hired despite his objections as a \\\\\\"burglar\\\\\\" by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istari\\\\\\">wizard</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_The_Hobbit_characters#Thorin.27s_company\\\\\\">13 Dwarves</a>\\\\u00a0led by their king\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thorin_Oakenshield\\\\\\">Thorin Oakenshield</a>\\\\u00a0on a quest to reclaim the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lonely_Mountain\\\\\\">Lonely Mountain</a>\\\\u00a0and its treasure from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragon_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">dragon</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smaug\\\\\\">Smaug</a>. The adventure took Bilbo and the companions through the wilderness, to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">elf</a>\\\\u00a0haven of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, across the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>\\\\u00a0and the black forest of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>, to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esgaroth\\\\\\">Lake-town</a>\\\\u00a0in the middle of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Lake_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Long Lake</a>, and eventually to the Mountain itself. Here, after the dragon was killed and the Mountain was reclaimed, soon after that the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Five_Armies\\\\\\">Battle of Five Armies</a>\\\\u00a0took place.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In his journey, Bilbo encountered other fantastic creatures, including\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Troll_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">trolls</a>, elves,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_animals#Great_Spiders\\\\\\">giant spiders</a>, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beorn\\\\\\">man who can change shape into a bear</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">goblins</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eagle_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">eagles</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warg\\\\\\">wolves</a>\\\\u00a0and a slimy, murderous creature named\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gollum\\\\\\">Gollum</a>. Underground, near Gollum's lair, Bilbo accidentally found a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">magic ring of invisibility</a>, which he used to escape from Gollum.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>By the end of the journey, Bilbo had become wiser and more confident, having saved the day in many precarious situations. Bilbo's journey has been compared to a pilgrimage of grace. The Hobbit can be characterized as a \\\\\\"Christian\\\\u00a0<i>bildungsroman</i>\\\\u00a0which equates progress to wisdom gained in the form of a rite of passage.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0He rescued the dwarves from giant spiders with the magic ring and a short\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_weapons_and_armour#Sting\\\\\\">Elven-sword</a>\\\\u00a0he acquired. He used the ring to sneak around in dangerous places, as well as his wits to smuggle the dwarves out of the elves' prisons. When tensions arose over ownership of the recovered treasure, he tried unsuccessfully to bring the opposing sides to compromise, using the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Arkenstone\\\\\\">Arkenstone</a>, a stolen heirloom jewel, as leverage. This strained his relationship with Thorin, but the two were reconciled at Thorin's deathbed. At the end of the story, Bilbo returned to his home in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0only to find that several of his relatives, believing him to be dead, were trying to claim his home and possessions. In addition to becoming wealthy from his share of the dwarves' treasure, he found that he, like\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adam\\\\\\">Adam</a>, had traded respectability for experience and wisdom. At the end, Gandalf proclaims Bilbo is no longer the Hobbit he was. This is certainly true as Bilbo has fully matured. Continuing the pilgrimage theme, a true pilgrimage does not end at the destination, but rather when the wanderer is absolved, blessed, and ready to return home.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Lord of the Rings\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">The Fellowship of the Ring</a></i>, the first volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, begins with Bilbo's \\\\\\"eleventy-first\\\\\\" (111th) birthday, 60 years after the beginning of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. The main character of the novel is\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>, Bilbo's cousin,<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[nb 1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0who celebrates his 33rd birthday and legally comes of age on the same day.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a02989 (<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_Reckoning\\\\\\">S.R.</a>\\\\u00a01389), Bilbo, a lifelong bachelor, adopted Frodo, the orphaned son of his first cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primula_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Primula Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and his second cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drogo_Baggins\\\\\\">Drogo Baggins</a>, and made him his heir. Though Frodo was actually \\\\\\"his first\\\\u00a0<i>and</i>\\\\u00a0second\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cousin#Cousin_chart\\\\\\">cousin once removed</a>\\\\u00a0either way\\\\\\",<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0the two regarded each other as uncle and nephew.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>All this time Bilbo had kept his magic ring, with no idea of its significance, using it mostly to hide from his obnoxious cousins, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sackville-Baggins\\\\\\">Sackville-Bagginses</a>, when they came to visit.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>'s investigations revealed it to be the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0forged by the Dark Lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>. The Ring had prolonged Bilbo's life beyond the normal hobbit span, and at 111 he still looked 50. While the Ring did not initially corrupt him as it had its previous owners, it was beginning to affect him; over the years, it had begun to prey on his mind when out of his sight, and he lost sleep and felt \\\\\\"thin, sort of\\\\u00a0<i>stretched</i>\\\\u00a0\\\\u2026 like butter that has been scraped over too much bread\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>On the night of his and Frodo's birthday, Bilbo threw himself a party and invited all of the Shire. He signed his home,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>, and estate over to Frodo. He then gave a farewell address to his neighbors, at the end of which he put on the Ring and vanished from sight. As Bilbo prepared finally to leave the house, he reacted with panic and suspicion when Gandalf tried to persuade him to leave the Ring with Frodo. Bilbo refused to give up the Ring, referring to it as his \\\\\\"precious\\\\\\" \\\\u2013 just as Gollum had. Gandalf lost his temper with his old friend and talked some sense into him. Bilbo admitted he would have liked to be rid of the Ring, and he left it behind, becoming the first person to do so voluntarily. He left the Shire that night, and was never seen in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbiton\\\\\\">Hobbiton</a>\\\\u00a0again.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>His earlier adventure, his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eccentric_(behavior)\\\\\\">eccentric</a>\\\\u00a0habits as a hobbit, and his sudden disappearance led to the enduring figure of \\\\\\"Mad Baggins\\\\\\" in hobbit folklore, who disappeared with a flash and a bang and returned with gold and jewels.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Freed of the Ring's power over his senses, Bilbo travelled first to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, and then on to visit the dwarves of the Lonely Mountain. After he returned to Rivendell he spent much of the next 17 years living a pleasant life of retirement: eating, sleeping, writing poetry, and working on his memoirs,\\\\u00a0<i>There and Back Again</i>, known as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. He became a scholar of Elven lore, leaving behind the\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_languages_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elvish</a></i>, which forms the basis of what is known to us as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Silmarillion\\\\\\">The Silmarillion</a></i>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>When Frodo and his friends\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Samwise Gamgee</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>\\\\u00a0stopped in Rivendell on their quest to destroy the Ring, Bilbo was still alive but now visibly aged, the years having caught up with him after he surrendered the Ring. Upon seeing the Ring again, he suddenly tried to take it from Frodo; he returned to his senses when a terrified Frodo backed away, and he broke down in tears, apologizing for bringing the burden of the Ring onto Frodo.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>After the quest to destroy the Ring was fulfilled in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>, Gandalf and the four Hobbits visited Rivendell on their way back to the Shire and found Bilbo still living there. He gave Frodo a set of manuscripts that later became\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the Elvish</i>, and also gave Sam a small bag of gold that represented the last of his share from Smaug's vast hoard. Two years later Bilbo accompanied Gandalf,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>, and Frodo to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grey_Havens\\\\\\">Grey Havens</a>, there to take ship for\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tol_Eress%C3%ABa\\\\\\">Tol Eress\\\\u00eba</a>\\\\u00a0across the sea, on 29th 'September'\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a03021. He had already celebrated his 131st birthday by this time, surpassing the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Took\\\\\\">Old Took</a>\\\\u00a0by one year and becoming the oldest Hobbit ever in Middle-earth. (The natural lifespan of Hobbits is about 100 years.)<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-4\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\"}]", "title": "Bilbo", "host_experience_relationship": [{"pk": 41, "experiences": 10, "sort_order": 0, "host_page": 38}, {"pk": 42, "experiences": 23, "sort_order": 1, "host_page": 38}], "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:23:37.638Z", "host_place_relationship": [{"pk": 16, "place": 18, "host_page": 38}], "numchild": 0, "search_description": "", "locked": false, "path": "000100010001000F", "host_interest_relationship": [{"pk": 18, "host_interests": 9, "host_page": 38}], "pk": 38, "go_live_at": null, "slug": "bilbo", "owner": 1, "show_in_menus": false, "expire_at": null, "live": true, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-04-26T03:08:53.058Z", "url_path": "/homepage/index-page/bilbo/", "content_type": 12, "image": 27, "seo_title": "", "expired": false}	\N	38	1
119	f	2017-04-21 03:26:46.181+00	{"host_interest_relationship": [{"pk": 5, "host_page": 28, "host_interests": 1}], "content_type": 12, "live": true, "host_experience_relationship": [{"pk": 12, "experiences": 26, "host_page": 28, "sort_order": 0}, {"pk": 13, "experiences": 21, "host_page": 28, "sort_order": 1}, {"pk": 14, "experiences": 24, "host_page": 28, "sort_order": 2}, {"pk": 15, "experiences": 22, "host_page": 28, "sort_order": 3}], "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T21:40:27.266Z", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "search_description": "", "image": 19, "host_place_relationship": [{"pk": 6, "host_page": 28, "place": 15}], "expired": false, "go_live_at": null, "expire_at": null, "seo_title": "", "path": "0001000100010005", "locked": false, "numchild": 0, "depth": 4, "title": "\\u00c9owyn", "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>\\\\u00c9owyn is a fictional character in Tolkien's legendarium who appears in his most famous work, The Lord of the Rings. She is a noblewoman of Rohan who is described as a shieldmaiden.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Literature\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Two_Towers\\\\\\">The Two Towers</a></i>, \\\\u00c9owyn, a daughter of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Kings_of_Rohan#House_of_Eorl\\\\\\">House of Eorl</a>\\\\u00a0and the goddaughter of King\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Th%C3%A9oden\\\\\\">Th\\\\u00e9oden</a>\\\\u00a0of Rohan, is introduced in Meduseld, the king's hall at Edoras.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-hall-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0She was the daughter of Th\\\\u00e9odwyn (Th\\\\u00e9oden's sister) and \\\\u00c9omund and the sister of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89omer\\\\\\">\\\\u00c9omer</a>. When she was only seven years old, her father was killed fighting\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">orcs</a>\\\\u00a0and her mother died of grief. \\\\u00c9owyn and \\\\u00c9omer were raised in her uncle's household as if they were his own children.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Tolkien writes that she longed to win renown in battle\\\\u2014especially since she was royal\\\\u2014but being female, her duties were reckoned to be at Edoras.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-healing-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0When Th\\\\u00e9oden's mind was poisoned by his adviser\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gr%C3%ADma_Wormtongue\\\\\\">Gr\\\\u00edma Wormtongue</a>, \\\\u00c9owyn was obliged to care for her uncle, and his deterioration pained her deeply. To make matters worse, she was constantly harassed by Gr\\\\u00edma, who lusted after her. However, when\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0arrived, he freed Th\\\\u00e9oden from Wormtongue's influence.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"image\\", \\"value\\": {\\"caption\\": \\"\\", \\"image\\": 35, \\"style\\": \\"\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>\\\\u00c9owyn fell in love with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>, but it soon became clear that he could not return her love although he did not mention his betrothal to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arwen\\\\\\">Arwen</a>, except by indirect allusion, and would not allow her to join him in going to war.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a>\\\\u00a0As Aragorn pointed out,<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a>\\\\u00a0her duty was with her hosts; she had to shoulder the responsibility of ruling Rohan in Th\\\\u00e9oden's stead when the war-host of Rohan went to war,<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-hall-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0a duty he deemed no less valiant.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a>\\\\u00a0Likening her situation to a \\\\\\"cage\\\\\\", \\\\u00c9owyn said she feared \\\\\\"[t]o stay behind bars, until use and old age accept them, and all chance of great deeds is gone beyond recall or desire.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\", \\"value\\": {\\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\", \\"text\\": \\"But who knows what she spoke to the darkness, alone, in the bitter watches of the night, when all her life seemed shrinking, and the walls of her bower closing in about her, a hutch to trammel some wild thing in?\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"Aragorn\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a>\\\\u00a0</i>she disguised herself as a man and under the alias of\\\\u00a0<i>Dernhelm</i>\\\\u00a0(from Old English\\\\u00a0<i>dern</i>\\\\u00a0meaning \\\\\\"secret, concealed\\\\\\"), and she traveled with the Riders of Rohan to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">Battle of the Pelennor Fields</a>\\\\u00a0outside the White City of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minas_Tirith\\\\\\">Minas Tirith</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>, carrying with her\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>, who had also been ordered to remain behind, on her horse Windfola.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>During the battle of the Pelennor Fields, she confronted the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>, Lord of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>, after Th\\\\u00e9oden was injured. The Witch-king threatened to \\\\\\"bear [her] away to the houses of lamentation, beyond all darkness, where [her] flesh shall be devoured, and [her] shriveled mind be left naked to the Lidless Eye.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0The Witch-king further boasted that \\\\\\"[n]o living man may hinder me,\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0referring to the 1,000-year-old\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prophecy\\\\\\">prophecy</a>\\\\u00a0by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elf</a>-lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glorfindel\\\\\\">Glorfindel</a>, foretelling that the Witch-king would not fall \\\\\\"by the hand of man\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-glorfindel-5\\\\\\">[5]</a>\\\\u00a0\\\\u00c9owyn then removed her helmet and declared.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>But no living man am I! You look upon a woman. \\\\u00c9owyn I am, \\\\u00c9omund\\\\u2019s daughter. You stand between me and my lord and kin. Begone, if you be not deathless! For living or dark undead, I will smite you, if you touch him.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The Witch-king attacked \\\\u00c9owyn with his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl#Steeds\\\\\\">steed</a>, but she slew it with her sword. He then shattered her shield and broke her shield-arm with his mace, but was distracted by Merry, who stabbed him behind the knee with a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow-blade\\\\\\">barrow-blade</a>. \\\\u00c9owyn seized the opportunity to strike the Witch-king with a killing thrust \\\\\\"between crown and mantle\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Then, as her sword shattered, his withering form collapsed and he vanished with a final cry of anguish.</p>\\"}]", "owner": 1, "show_in_menus": false, "url_path": "/homepage/index-page/\\u00e9owyn/", "pk": 28, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-23T07:43:39.036Z", "slug": "\\u00e9owyn"}	\N	28	1
