d thing in?\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a>\\\\u00a0</i>she disguised herself as a man and under the alias of\\\\u00a0<i>Dernhelm</i>\\\\u00a0(from Old English\\\\u00a0<i>dern</i>\\\\u00a0meaning \\\\\\"secret, concealed\\\\\\"), and she traveled with the Riders of Rohan to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">Battle of the Pelennor Fields</a>\\\\u00a0outside the White City of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minas_Tirith\\\\\\">Minas Tirith</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>, carrying with her\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>, who had also been ordered to remain behind, on her horse Windfola.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>During the battle of the Pelennor Fields, she confronted the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>, Lord of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>, after Th\\\\u00e9oden was injured. The Witch-king threatened to \\\\\\"bear [her] away to the houses of lamentation, beyond all darkness, where [her] flesh shall be devoured, and [her] shriveled mind be left naked to the Lidless Eye.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0The Witch-king further boasted that \\\\\\"[n]o living man may hinder me,\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0referring to the 1,000-year-old\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prophecy\\\\\\">prophecy</a>\\\\u00a0by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elf</a>-lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glorfindel\\\\\\">Glorfindel</a>, foretelling that the Witch-king would not fall \\\\\\"by the hand of man\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-glorfindel-5\\\\\\">[5]</a>\\\\u00a0\\\\u00c9owyn then removed her helmet and declared.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>But no living man am I! You look upon a woman. \\\\u00c9owyn I am, \\\\u00c9omund\\\\u2019s daughter. You stand between me and my lord and kin. Begone, if you be not deathless! For living or dark undead, I will smite you, if you touch him.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The Witch-king attacked \\\\u00c9owyn with his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl#Steeds\\\\\\">steed</a>, but she slew it with her sword. He then shattered her shield and broke her shield-arm with his mace, but was distracted by Merry, who stabbed him behind the knee with a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow-blade\\\\\\">barrow-blade</a>. \\\\u00c9owyn seized the opportunity to strike the Witch-king with a killing thrust \\\\\\"between crown and mantle\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Then, as her sword shattered, his withering form collapsed and he vanished with a final cry of anguish.</p>\\"}]", "title": "\\u00c9owyn", "host_experience_relationship": [{"pk": 12, "experiences": 26, "sort_order": 0, "host_page": 28}, {"pk": 13, "experiences": 21, "sort_order": 1, "host_page": 28}, {"pk": 14, "experiences": 24, "sort_order": 2, "host_page": 28}, {"pk": 15, "experiences": 22, "sort_order": 3, "host_page": 28}], "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T21:40:27.266Z", "host_place_relationship": [{"pk": 6, "place": 15, "host_page": 28}], "numchild":