stead when the war-host of Rohan went to war,<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-hall-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0a duty he deemed no less valiant.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a>\\\\u00a0Likening her situation to a \\\\\\"cage\\\\\\", \\\\u00c9owyn said she feared \\\\\\"[t]o stay behind bars, until use and old age accept them, and all chance of great deeds is gone beyond recall or desire.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"text\\": \\"But who knows what she spoke to the darkness, alone, in the bitter watches of the night, when all her life seemed shrinking, and the walls of her bower closing in about her, a hutch to trammel some wild thing in?\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"Aragorn\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a>\\\\u00a0</i>she disguised herself as a man and under the alias of\\\\u00a0<i>Dernhelm</i>\\\\u00a0(from Old English\\\\u00a0<i>dern</i>\\\\u00a0meaning \\\\\\"secret, concealed\\\\\\"), and she traveled with the Riders of Rohan to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">Battle of the Pelennor Fields</a>\\\\u00a0outside the White City of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minas_Tirith\\\\\\">Minas Tirith</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>, carrying with her\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>, who had also been ordered to remain behind, on her horse Windfola.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>During the battle of the Pelennor Fields, she confronted the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>, Lord of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>, after Th\\\\u00e9oden was injured. The Witch-king threatened to \\\\\\"bear [her] away to the houses of lamentation, beyond all darkness, where [her] flesh shall be devoured, and [her] shriveled mind be left naked to the Lidless Eye.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0The Witch-king further boasted that \\\\\\"[n]o living man may hinder me,\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0referring to the 1,000-year-old\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prophecy\\\\\\">prophecy</a>\\\\u00a0by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elf</a>-lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glorfindel\\\\\\">Glorfindel</a>, foretelling that the Witch-king would not fall \\\\\\"by the hand of man\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-glorfindel-5\\\\\\">[5]</a>\\\\u00a0\\\\u00c9owyn then removed her helmet and declared.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>But no living man am I! You look upon a woman. \\\\u00c9owyn I am, \\\\u00c9omund\\\\u2019s daughter. You stand between me and my lord and kin. Begone, if you be not deathless! For living or dark undead, I will smite you, if you touch him.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>The Witch-king attacked \\\\u00c9owyn with his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl#Steeds\\\\\\">steed</a>, but she slew it with her sword. He then shattered her shield and broke her shield-arm with his mace, but was distracted by Merry, who stabbed him behind the knee with a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow-blade\\\\\\">barrow-blade</a>. \\\\u00c9owyn seized the opportunity to strike the Witch-king with a killing thrust \\\\\\"between crown and mantle\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Then, as her sword shattered, his withering form collapsed and he vanished with a final cry of anguish.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T21:40:27.266Z"}	\N	28	1
