\">orcs</a>\\\\u00a0and her mother died of grief. \\\\u00c9owyn and \\\\u00c9omer were raised in her uncle's household as if they were his own children.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Tolkien writes that she longed to win renown in battle\\\\u2014especially since she was royal\\\\u2014but being female, her duties were reckoned to be at Edoras.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-healing-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0When Th\\\\u00e9oden's mind was poisoned by his adviser\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gr%C3%ADma_Wormtongue\\\\\\">Gr\\\\u00edma Wormtongue</a>, \\\\u00c9owyn was obliged to care for her uncle, and his deterioration pained her deeply. To make matters worse, she was constantly harassed by Gr\\\\u00edma, who lusted after her. However, when\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0arrived, he freed Th\\\\u00e9oden from Wormtongue's influence.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>\\\\u00c9owyn fell in love with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>, but it soon became clear that he could not return her love although he did not mention his betrothal to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arwen\\\\\\">Arwen</a>, except by indirect allusion, and would not allow her to join him in going to war.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a>\\\\u00a0As Aragorn pointed out,<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a>\\\\u00a0her duty was with her hosts; she had to shoulder the responsibility of ruling Rohan in Th\\\\u00e9oden's stead when the war-host of Rohan went to war,<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-hall-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0a duty he deemed no less valiant.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a>\\\\u00a0Likening her situation to a \\\\\\"cage\\\\\\", \\\\u00c9owyn said she feared \\\\\\"[t]o stay behind bars, until use and old age accept them, and all chance of great deeds is gone beyond recall or desire.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-grey-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\", \\"value\\": {\\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"Aragorn\\", \\"text\\": \\"But who knows what she spoke to the darkness, alone, in the bitter watches of the night, when all her life seemed shrinking, and the walls of her bower closing in about her, a hutch to trammel some wild thing in?\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a>\\\\u00a0</i>she disguised herself as a man and under the alias of\\\\u00a0<i>Dernhelm</i>\\\\u00a0(from Old English\\\\u00a0<i>dern</i>\\\\u00a0meaning \\\\\\"secret, concealed\\\\\\"), and she traveled with the Riders of Rohan to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">Battle of the Pelennor Fields</a>\\\\u00a0outside the White City of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minas_Tirith\\\\\\">Minas Tirith</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>, carrying with her\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>, who had also been ordered to remain behind, on her horse Windfola.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>During the battle of the Pelennor Fields, she confronted the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>, Lord of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>, after Th\\\\u00e9oden was injured. The Witch-king threatened to \\\\\\"bear [her] away to the houses of lamentation, beyond all darkness, where [her] flesh shall be devoured, and [her] shriveled mind be left naked to the Lidless Eye.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0The Witch-king further boasted that \\\\\\"[n]o living man may hinder me,\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0referring to the 1,000-year-old\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prophecy\\\\\\">prophecy</a>\\\\u00a0by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elf</a>-lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glorfindel\\\\\\">Glorfindel</a>, foretelling that the Witch-king would not fall \\\\\\"by the hand of man\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-glorfindel-5\\\\\\">[5]</a>\\\\u00a0\\\\u00c9owyn then removed her helmet and declared.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>But no living man am I! You look upon a woman. \\\\u00c9owyn I am, \\\\u00c9omund\\\\u2019s daughter. You stand between me and my lord and kin. Begone, if you be not deathless! For living or dark undead, I will smite you, if you touch him.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The Witch-king attacked \\\\u00c9owyn with his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl#Steeds\\\\\\">steed</a>, but she slew it with her sword. He then shattered her shield and broke her shield-arm with his mace, but was distracted by Merry, who stabbed him behind the knee with a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow-blade\\\\\\">barrow-blade</a>. \\\\u00c9owyn seized the opportunity to strike the Witch-king with a killing thrust \\\\\\"between crown and mantle\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn#cite_note-pelennor-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Then, as her sword shattered, his withering form collapsed and he vanished with a final cry of anguish.</p>\\"}]", "depth": 4, "live": true, "host_interests": [{"content_object": 28, "tag": 4, "pk": null}, {"content_object": 28, "tag": 5, "pk": null}, {"content_object": 28, "tag": 6, "pk": null}], "host_experience_relationship": [{"sort_order": 0, "experiences": 26, "host_page": 28, "pk": 12}, {"sort_order": 1, "experiences": 21, "host_page": 28, "pk": 13}, {"sort_order": 2, "experiences": 24, "host_page": 28, "pk": 14}, {"sort_order": 3, "experiences": 22, "host_page": 28, "pk": 15}], "pk": 28, "image": 19, "show_in_menus": false, "expired": false}	\N	28	1
287	f	2018-01-26 04:04:25.266679+00	{"path": "0001000100030002", "go_live_at": null, "content_type": 6, "depth": 4, "show_in_menus": false, "image": 41, "numchild": 0, "first_published_at": "2017-01-09T10:57:05.960Z", "seo_title": "", "search_description": "", "live": true, "slug": "inle", "expired": false, "title": "Inle", "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Inle Lake is a shallow lake in the middle of Myanmar, south-east of Mandalay. The lake is 22km long, and is densely inhabited by many different tribes.<br/></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"image\\", \\"value\\": {\\"style\\": \\"full\\", \\"image\\": 69, \\"caption\\": \\"Inle Paungdaw Oo Pagoda\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The easiest way to get into Inle Lake (and the most comfortable) is by domestic flight. The closest airport is in Heho, which is a taxi-ride (about 1 hour) away from the lake itself (walking down the road from the airport, towards the highway, should see quoted fares drop, if not, try your luck hailing a taxi or passing pickup on the highway itself). Taking a taxi from the airport is expensive, as of January 2017 there is a fixed, non-bargainable price of 25,000 Kyats to go to Nyuang Shwe. If you baulk at the high fare, the taxi drivers will attempt to gather other travelers to share the taxi and split the fare, so there is a good chance you will end up paying a lot less by sharing your taxi. By comparison a taxi from Yangon airport to the city centre (45 min.) is just 8000 Kyats or 7 USD. A possible way to save money is to book a taxi in advance with your guesthouse, but seems like now they all charge the same 25,000 kyat fixed price. 15,000kyat is a good price to/from the airport that may be more difficult to reserve on your way in, but no issue to book for your return trip to Heho from any agency in town. When returning, you can often save by booking a shared taxi through your hotel or one of the many travel agents around. Check with them the day before you fly out.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Prices for flights are around US$110 from Yangon and US$75 from Mandalay, but unlike bus companies the government is heavily involved in the domestic air market, a good chunk of your money will be going into their hands.</p>\\"}]", "expire_at": null, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-06-13T03:19:56.142Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 12, "url_path": "/homepage/places/inle/", "locked": false}	\N	12	1
