tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0known also as Merry and Pippin.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0Treebeard is known to have a strong hatred of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Orcs</a>, and, after Saruman's betrayal of the Ents, of Saruman as well.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0During his initial encounter with the two hobbits, he is so agitated that he misidentifies them as orc spies. He then carries them to the white wizard.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Spirits were sent by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eru_Il%C3%BAvatar\\\\\\">Eru Il\\\\u00favatar</a>\\\\u00a0to inhabit the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree\\\\\\">trees</a>, which the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vala_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Vala</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yavanna\\\\\\">Yavanna</a>\\\\u00a0had created along with other plants or\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_plants\\\\\\">olvar</a></i>. The Vala longed for their protection since\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morgoth\\\\\\">Morgoth</a>\\\\u00a0or\\\\u00a0<i>Melkor</i>\\\\u00a0was destroying the trees and olvar, which could not defend themselves from him. The Ents were created by Il\\\\u00favatar at the behest of Yavanna as the\\\\u00a0<i>Shepherds of the Forest</i>\\\\u00a0or\\\\u00a0<i>Tree-herders</i>.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ent#Entwives\\\\\\">Entwives</a>\\\\u00a0were also created for the Ents, but, in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Age\\\\\\">Second Age</a>, were driven out by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup><sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a></sup><sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Treebeard is the oldest of three remaining original Ents.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0He is said to have once roamed all of the forests in Middle-earth, which included the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mordor\\\\\\">Mordor</a>, and the Blue Mountains. After the loss of the Entwives by the end of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">Third Age</a>, he and the remaining Ents dwelt in the Forest of Fangorn. This led the remaining Ents into isolation and all information from the outside world was cut off.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0The arrival of Merry and Pippin shifted Treebeard's attention to take action against Saruman for hacking down his trees. He led the Ents to war against Saruman and his Orcs. Treebeard later realised that while Saruman had learned much from him, the Wizard had shared no useful information of his own.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"text\\": \\"A large Man-like figure, at least fourteen foot high, very sturdy, with a tall head, and hardly any neck. Whether it was clad in stuff like green and grey bark, or whether that was its hide, was difficult to say. Arms, at a short distance from the trunk, were not wrinkled, but covered with a brown smooth skin. The large feet had seven toes each. Grey beard, deep brown eyes, shot with a green light.\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"JRR Tolkien\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Treebeard had been friends with Saruman. It is described in\\\\u00a0<i>The Two Towers</i>\\\\u00a0that Saruman visited Treebeard in Fangorn Forest and had talked with him on various subjects of concern. Saruman gathered information from Treebeard about the Forest of Fangorn; its intertwining paths were of particular concern to him.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After Merry and Pippin's meeting with Treebeard, Treebeard called an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entmoot\\\\\\">Entmoot</a>, which lasted three days, to decide to call an attack on Isengard and Saruman.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Since\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leaflock\\\\\\">Leaflock</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skinbark\\\\\\">Skinbark</a>\\\\u00a0were the oldest of the Ents along with Treebeard, they refused to fight, however, Treebeard thought he was going to his doom during \\\\\\"the last march of the Ents.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Treebeard hoped that some of the younger Ents would come instead of just the two, and, during the night he spread the word. They later launched an assault on Isengard.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/BbV2Hr0qRdo\\", \\"type\\": \\"embed\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After Treebeard ordered the Ents to march to Isengard, the Ents felled Saruman's walls and destroyed every object in and around Isengard; the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthanc\\\\\\">Tower of Orthanc</a>\\\\u00a0could not be breached, but Saruman was trapped within. Treebeard stopped the attack on the tower when he realised their efforts were in vain; the tower was too strong. The Ents were ordered to unleash the waters of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_rivers#I\\\\\\">River Isen</a>, which flooded Isengard.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0When Merry and Pippin departed Treebeard he requested them to watch for the Entwives.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0At one point in the book, Tolkien gives hints on the whereabouts of the Entwives. It is speculated that they were spotted by Samwise Gamgee's cousin Hal in the North Farthing.\\\\u00a0</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-20T22:05:52.384Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 30, "path": "0001000100010007", "content_type": 12, "depth": 4, "slug": "moe-htwe", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T21:49:00.050Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/moe-htwe/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": false, "has_unpu