https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0known also as Merry and Pippin.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0Treebeard is known to have a strong hatred of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Orcs</a>, and, after Saruman's betrayal of the Ents, of Saruman as well.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0During his initial encounter with the two hobbits, he is so agitated that he misidentifies them as orc spies. He then carries them to the white wizard.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Spirits were sent by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eru_Il%C3%BAvatar\\\\\\">Eru Il\\\\u00favatar</a>\\\\u00a0to inhabit the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree\\\\\\">trees</a>, which the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vala_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Vala</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yavanna\\\\\\">Yavanna</a>\\\\u00a0had created along with other plants or\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_plants\\\\\\">olvar</a></i>. The Vala longed for their protection since\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morgoth\\\\\\">Morgoth</a>\\\\u00a0or\\\\u00a0<i>Melkor</i>\\\\u00a0was destroying the trees and olvar, which could not defend themselves from him. The Ents were created by Il\\\\u00favatar at the behest of Yavanna as the\\\\u00a0<i>Shepherds of the Forest</i>\\\\u00a0or\\\\u00a0<i>Tree-herders</i>.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ent#Entwives\\\\\\">Entwives</a>\\\\u00a0were also created for the Ents, but, in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Age\\\\\\">Second Age</a>, were driven out by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup><sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a></sup><sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Treebeard is the oldest of three remaining original Ents.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0He is said to have once roamed all of the forests in Middle-earth, which included the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mordor\\\\\\">Mordor</a>, and the Blue Mountains. After the loss of the Entwives by the end of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">Third Age</a>, he and the remaining Ents dwelt in the Forest of Fangorn. This led the remaining Ents into isolation and all information from the outside world was cut off.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0The arrival of Merry and Pippin shifted Treebeard's attention to take action against Saruman for hacking down his trees. He led the Ents to war against Saruman and his Orcs. Treebeard later realised that while Saruman had learned much from him, the Wizard had shared no useful information of his own.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"text\\": \\"A large Man-like figure, at least fourteen foot high, very sturdy, with a tall head, and hardly any neck. Whether it was clad in stuff like green and grey bark, or whether that was its hide, was difficult to say. Arms, at a short distance from the trunk, were not wrinkled, but covered with a brown smooth skin. The large feet had seven toes each. Grey beard, deep brown eyes, shot with a green light.\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"JRR Tolkien\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Treebeard had been friends with Saruman. It is described in\\\\u00a0<i>The Two Towers</i>\\\\u00a0that Saruman visited Treebeard in Fangorn Forest and had talked with him on various subjects of concern. Saruman gathered information from Treebeard about the Forest of Fangorn; its intertwining paths were of particular concern to him.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After Merry and Pippin's meeting with Treebeard, Treebeard called an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entmoot\\\\\\">Entmoot</a>, which lasted three days, to decide to call an attack on Isengard and Saruman.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Since\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leaflock\\\\\\">Leaflock</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skinbark\\\\\\">Skinbark</a>\\\\u00a0were the oldest of the Ents along with Treebeard, they refused to fight, however, Treebeard thought he was going to his doom during \\\\\\"the last march of the Ents.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Treebeard hoped that some of the younger Ents would come instead of just the two, and, during the night he spread the word. They later launched an assault on Isengard.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/BbV2Hr0qRdo\\", \\"type\\": \\"embed\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After Treebeard ordered the Ents to march to Isengard, the Ents felled Saruman's walls and destroyed every object in and around Isengard; the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthanc\\\\\\">Tower of Orthanc</a>\\\\u00a0could not be breached, but Saruman was trapped within. Treebeard stopped the attack on the tower when he realised their efforts were in vain; the tower was too strong. The Ents were ordered to unleash the waters of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_rivers#I\\\\\\">River Isen</a>, which flooded Isengard.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0When Merry and Pippin departed Treebeard he requested them to watch for the Entwives.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0At one point in the book, Tolkien gives hints on the whereabouts of the Entwives. It is speculated that they were spotted by Samwise Gamgee's cousin Hal in the North Farthing.\\\\u00a0</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-20T22:06:48.084Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 30, "path": "0001000100010007", "content_type": 12, "depth": 4, "slug": "moe-htwe", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T21:49:00.050Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/moe-htwe/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": false, "has_unpublished_changes": true, "title": "Moe Htwe", "locked": false}	\N	30	2
240	f	2018-01-20 22:08:08.764231+00	{"host_language_relationship": [], "expired": false, "image": 56, "expire_at": null, "body": "[{\\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Bilbo Baggins</b>\\\\u00a0is the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Title_character\\\\\\">title character</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protagonist\\\\\\">protagonist</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s 1937 novel\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>, as well as a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supporting_character\\\\\\">supporting character</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>. In Tolkien's narrative\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conceit\\\\\\">conceit</a>, in which all the writings of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>\\\\u00a0are translations from the fictitious volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Book_of_Westmarch\\\\\\">Red Book of Westmarch</a></i>, Bilbo is the author of\\\\u00a0<i>The Hobbit</i>\\\\u00a0and translator of various \\\\\\"works from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_language\\\\\\">elvish</a>\\\\\\" (as mentioned in the end of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>).</p><p></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Hobbit\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"caption\\": \\"Bilbo Baggins illustration\\", \\"style\\": \\"half\\", \\"image\\": 28}, \\"type\\": \\"image\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i>The Hobbit</i>, Bilbo Baggins, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">hobbit</a>\\\\u00a0in comfortable middle age at 50 years old, was hired despite his objections as a \\\\\\"burglar\\\\\\" by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istari\\\\\\">wizard</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_The_Hobbit_characters#Thorin.27s_company\\\\\\">13 Dwarves</a>\\\\u00a0led by their king\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thorin_Oakenshield\\\\\\">Thorin Oakenshield</a>\\\\u00a0on a quest to reclaim the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lonely_Mountain\\\\\\">Lonely Mountain</a>\\\\u00a0and its treasure from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragon_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">dragon</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smaug\\\\\\">Smaug</a>. The adventure took Bilbo and the companions through the wilderness, to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">elf</a>\\\\u00a0haven of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, across the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>\\\\u00a0and the black forest of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>, to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esgaroth\\\\\\">Lake-town</a>\\\\u00a0in the middle of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Lake_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Long Lake</a>, and eventually to the Mountain itself. Here, after the dragon was killed and the Mountain was reclaimed, soon after that the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Five_Armies\\\\\\">Battle of Five Armies</a>\\\\u00a0took place.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In his journey, Bilbo encountered other fantastic creatures, including\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Troll_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">trolls</a>, elves,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_animals#Great_Spiders\\\\\\">giant spiders</a>, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beorn\\\\\\">man who can change shape into a bear</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">goblins</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eagle_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">eagles</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warg\\\\\\">wolves</a>\\\\u00a0and a slimy, murderous creature named\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gollum\\\\\\">Gollum</a>. Underground, near Gollum's lair, Bilbo accidentally found a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">magic ring of invisibility</a>, which he used to escape from Gollum.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>By the end of the journey, Bilbo had become wiser and more confident, having saved the day in many precarious situations. Bilbo's journey has been compared to a pilgrimage of grace. The Hobbit can be characterized as a \\\\\\"Christian\\\\u00a0<i>bildungsroman</i>\\\\u00a0which equates progress to wisdom gained in the form of a rite of passage.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0He rescued the dwarves from giant spiders with the magic ring and a short\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_weapons_and_armour#Sting\\\\\\">Elven-sword</a>\\\\u00a0he acquired. He used the ring to sneak around in dangerous places, as well as his wits to smuggle the dwarves out of the elves' prisons. When tensions arose over ownership of the recovered treasure, he tried unsuccessfully to bring the opposing sides to compromise, using the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Arkenstone\\\\\\">Arkenstone</a>, a stolen heirloom jewel, as leverage. This strained his relationship with Thorin, but the two were reconciled at Thorin's deathbed. At the end of the story, Bilbo returned to his home in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0only to find that several of his relatives, believing him to be dead, were trying to claim his home and possessions. In addition to becoming wealthy from his share of the dwarves' treasure, he found that he, like\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adam\\\\\\">Adam</a>, had traded respectability for experience and wisdom. At the end, Gandalf proclaims Bilbo is no longer the Hobbit he was. This is certainly true as Bilbo has fully matured. Continuing the pilgrimage theme, a true pilgrimage does not end at the destination, but rather when the wanderer is absolved, blessed, and ready to return home.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Lord of the Rings\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p><i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">The Fellowship of the Ring</a></i>, the first volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, begins with Bilbo's \\\\\\"eleventy-first\\\\\\" (111th) birthday, 60 years after the beginning of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. The main character of the novel is\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>, Bilbo's cousin,<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[nb 1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0who celebrates his 33rd birthday and legally comes of age on the same day.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a02989 (<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_Reckoning\\\\\\">S.R.</a>\\\\u00a01389), Bilbo, a lifelong bachelor, adopted Frodo, the orphaned son of his first cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primula_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Primula Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and his second cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drogo_Baggins\\\\\\">Drogo Baggins</a>, and made him his heir. Though Frodo was actually \\\\\\"his first\\\\u00a0<i>and</i>\\\\u00a0second\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cousin#Cousin_chart\\\\\\">cousin once removed</a>\\\\u00a0either way\\\\\\",<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0the two regarded each other as uncle and nephew.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>All this time Bilbo had kept his magic ring, with no idea of its significance, using it mostly to hide from his obnoxious cousins, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sackville-Baggins\\\\\\">Sackville-Bagginses</a>, when they came to visit.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>'s investigations revealed it to be the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0forged by the Dark Lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>. The Ring had prolonged Bilbo's life beyond the normal hobbit span, and at 111 he still looked 50. While the Ring did not initially corrupt him as it had its previous owners, it was beginning to affect him; over the years, it had begun to prey on his mind when out of his sight, and he lost sleep and felt \\\\\\"thin, sort of\\\\u00a0<i>stretched</i>\\\\u00a0\\\\u2026 like butter that has been scraped over too much bread\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>On the night of his and Frodo's birthday, Bilbo threw himself a party and invited all of the Shire. He signed his home,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>, and estate over to Frodo. He then gave a farewell address to his neighbors, at the end of which he put on the Ring and vanished from sight. As Bilbo prepared finally to leave the house, he reacted with panic and suspicion when Gandalf tried to persuade him to leave the Ring with Frodo. Bilbo refused to give up the Ring, referring to it as his \\\\\\"precious\\\\\\" \\\\u2013 just as Gollum had. Gandalf lost his temper with his old friend and talked some sense into him. Bilbo admitted he would have liked to be rid of the Ring, and he left it behind, becoming the first person to do so voluntarily. He left the Shire that night, and was never seen in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbiton\\\\\\">Hobbiton</a>\\\\u00a0again.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>His earlier adventure, his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eccentric_(behavior)\\\\\\">eccentric</a>\\\\u00a0habits as a hobbit, and his sudden disappearance led to the enduring figure of \\\\\\"Mad Baggins\\\\\\" in hobbit folklore, who disappeared with a flash and a bang and returned with gold and jewels.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Freed of the Ring's power over his senses, Bilbo travelled first to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, and then on to visit the dwarves of the Lonely Mountain. After he returned to Rivendell he spent much of the next 17 years living a pleasant life of retirement: eating, sleeping, writing poetry, and working on his memoirs,\\\\u00a0<i>There and Back Again</i>, known as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. He became a scholar of Elven lore, leaving behind the\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_languages_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elvish</a></i>, which forms the basis of what is known to us as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Silmarillion\\\\\\">The Silmarillion</a></i>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>When Frodo and his friends\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Samwise Gamgee</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>\\\\u00a0stopped in Rivendell on their quest to destroy the Ring, Bilbo was still alive but now visibly aged, the years having caught up with him after he surrendered the Ring. Upon seeing the Ring again, he suddenly tried to take it from Frodo; he returned to his senses when a terrified Frodo backed away, and he broke down in tears, apologizing for bringing the burden of the Ring onto Frodo.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After the quest to destroy the Ring was fulfilled in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>, Gandalf and the four Hobbits visited Rivendell on their way back to the Shire and found Bilbo still living there. He gave Frodo a set of manuscripts that later became\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the Elvish</i>, and also gave Sam a small bag of gold that represented the last of his share from Smaug's vast hoard. Two years later Bilbo accompanied Gandalf,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>, and Frodo to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grey_Havens\\\\\\">Grey Havens</a>, there to take ship for\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tol_Eress%C3%ABa\\\\\\">Tol Eress\\\\u00eba</a>\\\\u00a0across the sea, on 29th 'September'\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a03021. He had already celebrated his 131st birthday by this time, surpassing the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Took\\\\\\">Old Took</a>\\\\u00a0by one year and becoming the oldest Hobbit ever in Middle-earth. (The natural lifespan of Hobbits is about 100 years.)<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-4\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-20T21:56:16.706Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 38, "path": "000100010001000F", "content_type": 12, "depth": 4, "slug": "tun", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:23:37.638Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/tun/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "test.boo2@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": false, "has_unpublished_changes": true, "title": "Than Tun", "locked": false}	\N	38	2
