81	f	2017-01-23 07:21:34.397+00	{"host_place_relationship": [{"place": 18, "host_page": 36, "pk": 14}], "pk": 36, "url_path": "/homepage/index-page/samwise-gamgee/", "go_live_at": null, "live": true, "content_type": 12, "numchild": 0, "expired": false, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Samwise</b>\\\\u00a0\\\\\\"<b>Sam</b>\\\\\\"\\\\u00a0<b>Gamgee</b>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English\\\\\\">/\\\\u02c8s\\\\u00e6m\\\\u02ccwa\\\\u026az\\\\u00a0\\\\u02c8\\\\u0261\\\\u00e6m\\\\u02ccd\\\\u0292i\\\\u02d0/</a>\\\\u00a0(later known as Samwise Gardner)<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee#cite_note-gardner-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0is a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fictional_character\\\\\\">fictional character</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tolkien%27s_legendarium\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien's legendarium</a>. Samwise is one of the main characters of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>, in which he fills an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archetype\\\\\\">archetypical</a>\\\\u00a0role as the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidekick\\\\\\">sidekick</a>\\\\u00a0of the primary\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protagonist\\\\\\">protagonist</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>. Sam is a member of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship of the Ring</a>.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Literature\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Samwise Gamgee is first introduced in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">The Fellowship of the Ring</a></i>. Sam is\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>' gardener, having inherited the position as Baggins' gardener from his father,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaffer_Gamgee\\\\\\">Hamfast \\\\\\"Gaffer\\\\\\" Gamgee</a>. At the time of the War of the Ring, Sam was living in Number 3,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_roads#Bagshot_Row\\\\\\">Bagshot Row</a>\\\\u00a0with his father.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>As \\\\\\"punishment\\\\\\" for\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eavesdropping\\\\\\">eavesdropping</a>\\\\u00a0on\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>'s conversation with Frodo regarding the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>, Sam was made Frodo's first companion on his journey to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>. They were joined by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>, Frodo's cousins, and journeyed together to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, where the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Elrond\\\\\\">Council of Elrond</a>\\\\u00a0took place and Sam joined the Fellowship of the Ring.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\", \\"value\\": {\\"attribute_name\\": \\"Samwise Gamgee\\", \\"text\\": \\"'Come, Mr. Frodo!' he cried. 'I can't carry it for you, but I can carry you.'\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"Return of the King\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>When the Fellowship was split up at the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Falls_of_Rauros\\\\\\">Falls of Rauros</a>, Sam insisted on accompanying Frodo. Sam protected and cared for Frodo, who was growing weaker under the Ring's influence, as they moved through the dangerous lands toward\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mordor\\\\\\">Mordor</a>. Sam distrusted\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gollum\\\\\\">Gollum</a>, who became their guide into Mordor. His suspicions were proven right when Gollum betrayed them to the giant spider\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shelob\\\\\\">Shelob</a>. After Shelob apparently killed Frodo, Sam drove her off. When a band of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">orcs</a>\\\\u00a0approached, Sam was forced to leave the apparently dead Frodo and take the Ring himself, and briefly became a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ring-bearer\\\\\\">Ring-bearer</a>. He was momentarily tempted by its promise of power, but did not succumb to it, subsequently rescuing Frodo (who had only been paralysed) from the Orcs who held him captive. Sam also returned the Ring to Frodo, making him the only Ring-bearer to freely give up the Ring without intervention. The two then journeyed alone through Mordor and into the heart of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Doom\\\\\\">Mount Doom</a>, where Gollum attacked Frodo and reclaimed the Ring, only to inadvertently destroy both it and himself by falling into the mountain's lava.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"embed\\", \\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/l1eLHoDxMNE\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>After the hobbits' return home and the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Bywater\\\\\\">Battle of Bywater</a>, Sam travelled the length and breadth of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0replanting trees that had been cut down during\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saruman\\\\\\">Saruman</a>'s brief reign. He used the gift of earth given to him by the Lady\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>, which caused the saplings he planted to grow at an accelerated rate. The small amount remaining he took to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three-Farthing_Stone\\\\\\">Three-Farthing Stone</a>\\\\u00a0(roughly the centre of the Shire) and cast into the air, prompting the bountiful period of growth starting in the spring of the year 1420 (<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_Reckoning\\\\\\">Shire Reckoning</a>). The greatest wonder was a young\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mallorn\\\\\\">mallorn</a></i>\\\\u00a0tree sprouting in the Party Field: \\\\\\"the only\\\\u00a0<i>mallorn</i>\\\\u00a0west of the Mountains and east of the Sea\\\\\\" (grown from a nut included as part of Galadriel's gift).</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>After the War of the Ring, Sam married\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#Rose_Cotton\\\\\\">Rose \\\\\\"Rosie\\\\\\" Cotton</a>\\\\u00a0and moved to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>\\\\u00a0with Frodo. Sam and Rosie had 13 children:\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elanor_the_Fair\\\\\\">Elanor the Fair</a>, Frodo, Rose, Merry, Pippin, Goldilocks, Hamfast, Daisy, Primrose, Bilbo, Ruby, Robin, and Tolman (Tom). Sam was elected\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mayor_of_the_Shire\\\\\\">Mayor of the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0for seven consecutive seven-year terms and came to be known as Samwise Gardner.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>After Sam and Rose's first child was born, Frodo told Sam he would leave\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>, along with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins\\\\\\">Bilbo Baggins</a>, Gandalf and most of the remaining High\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elves</a>, for the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Undying_Lands\\\\\\">Undying Lands</a>. Before Frodo left, he gave the estate of Bag End to Sam, as well as the\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Book_of_Westmarch\\\\\\">Red Book of Westmarch</a></i>\\\\u00a0for Sam to continue, hinting that Sam might also be allowed to travel into the West eventually.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>After the death of his wife in the year 62 of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fourth_Age\\\\\\">Fourth Age</a>\\\\u00a0(<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_Calendar\\\\\\">Shire Reckoning</a>\\\\u00a01482), Sam entrusted the Red Book to Elanor and left the Shire at the age of 102. He was not seen again in Middle-earth, but Elanor and her descendants preserved the tradition that he went to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grey_Havens\\\\\\">Grey Havens</a>\\\\u00a0and sailed into the West. As the last of the Ring-bearers, he was entitled to sail across the Sea and be reunited with Frodo in the Undying Lands.</p>\\"}]", "path": "000100010001000D", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-23T07:20:06.748Z", "image": 33, "host_interest_relationship": [{"host_interests": 4, "host_page": 36, "pk": 13}], "title": "Sam", "show_in_menus": false, "locked": false, "expire_at": null, "seo_title": "", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:13:58.009Z", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "depth": 4, "host_experience_relationship": [{"experiences": 26, "host_page": 36, "pk": 35, "sort_order": 0}, {"experiences": 23, "host_page": 36, "pk": 36, "sort_order": 1}, {"experiences": 22, "host_page": 36, "pk": 37, "sort_order": 2}], "owner": 1, "slug": "samwise-gamgee", "search_description": ""}	\N