231	f	2018-01-20 21:59:58.817694+00	{"host_language_relationship": [], "expired": false, "image": 59, "expire_at": null, "body": "[{\\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Meriadoc Brandybuck</b>, usually referred to as\\\\u00a0<b>Merry</b>, is a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fictional_character\\\\\\">fictional character</a>\\\\u00a0from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legendarium\\\\\\">legendarium</a>, featured throughout his most famous work,\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>A lover of boats and maps, Merry is described as one of the closest friends of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>, the main protagonist. Merry is a member of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship of the Ring</a>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"Family and relations\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Frodo and Merry are\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cousin#First_cousins\\\\\\">first cousins once removed</a>. Their common ancestors are\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#G\\\\\\">Gorbadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#M\\\\\\">Mirabella Took Brandybuck</a>.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck#cite_note-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Merry was born\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a02982 (or, in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth_calendar#Shire_calendar\\\\\\">Shire-reckoning</a>, in 1382), in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Buckland</a>.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0He is the only child of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#S\\\\\\">Saradoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0(T.A. 2940-<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fourth_Age\\\\\\">F.A.</a>\\\\u00a011), who was a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandybuck_Clan#Masters_of_Buckland\\\\\\">Master of Buckland</a>, and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#E\\\\\\">Esmeralda Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0(n\\\\u00e9e Took) (T.A. 2936-\\\\u00a0?), the younger sister of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#P\\\\\\">Paladin Took II</a>\\\\u00a0(T.A. 2933\\\\u20133034), making him first cousin to Paladin's son\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>. (See\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, Appendix C.)</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Merry later married\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Hobbits#E\\\\\\">Estella (Bolger) Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0(T.A. 2985\\\\u2013?), the younger sister of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fredegar_Bolger\\\\\\">Fredegar Bolger</a>, who helped Frodo, Sam, Merry and Pippin on the first leg of their quest journey. Meriadoc and Estella had at least one son.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck#cite_note-M-E_Encyc-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"Literature\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, Merry is often considered, and was described by Tolkien as, the most perceptive and intelligent of the hobbits. Even before\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins\\\\\\">Bilbo Baggins</a>\\\\u00a0left\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>, he knew of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0and its power of invisibility. He guarded\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>\\\\u00a0after Bilbo's party, protecting Frodo from the various and often unwanted guests. He is knowledgeable and has an innocent, teasing sense of humour. In one incident,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lobelia_Sackville-Baggins\\\\\\">Lobelia Sackville-Baggins</a>\\\\u00a0accused Frodo of being a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandybuck_clan\\\\\\">Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and no true\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_hobbit_families#B\\\\\\">Baggins</a>. Merry assured Frodo, \\\\\\"It was a compliment; and so, of course, not true\\\\\\".</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Merry was also a force behind \\\\\\"the Conspiracy\\\\\\" of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Sam</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Pippin</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fredegar_Bolger\\\\\\">Fredegar Bolger</a>\\\\u00a0and himself to help Frodo. Thus, at the beginning of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">The Fellowship of the Ring</a></i>, Merry was well-prepared and organized \\\\u2014 he assembled their packs and brought ponies. His shortcut through the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Forest\\\\\\">Old Forest</a>\\\\u00a0distanced them from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>\\\\u00a0for a time, though they had to be rescued from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Man_Willow\\\\\\">Old Man Willow</a>\\\\u00a0by the enigmatic\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Bombadil\\\\\\">Tom Bombadil</a>. In the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow-downs_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Barrow-downs</a>, he acquired his sword, which was actually a dagger forged in the kingdom of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arnor\\\\\\">Arnor</a>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>At\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bree_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Bree</a>, Merry was actually not present in the\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prancing_Pony\\\\\\">Prancing Pony</a></i>\\\\u00a0when Frodo put on the Ring; instead, he was outside taking a walk, and was nearly overcome by a Nazg\\\\u00fbl. At\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, he was seen studying maps and plotting their path. He was admitted to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship</a>\\\\u00a0only a little less reluctantly than Pippin; they were the two youngest members, and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>\\\\u00a0had planned on sending them back to the Shire.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/kTnQeasvbZo\\", \\"type\\": \\"embed\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>At the entrance to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moria_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Moria</a>, he asked\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0the meaning of the door inscription \\\\\\"Speak, friend, and enter\\\\\\". When Gandalf discovered the true interpretation, he said, \\\\\\"Merry, of all hosts, was on the right track\\\\\\".</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>At\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amon_Hen\\\\\\">Amon Hen</a>, he was captured, along with Pippin, by a band of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saruman\\\\\\">Saruman</a>'s\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uruk-hai\\\\\\">Uruk-hai</a>, although he gave a good account of himself and was valiantly defended by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boromir\\\\\\">Boromir</a>. Escaping with Pippin into\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fangorn\\\\\\">Fangorn</a>forest, Merry was rescued by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard\\\\\\">Treebeard</a>. Along with Pippin, he drank significant amounts of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ent-draught\\\\\\">Ent-draught</a>\\\\u00a0and grew taller, despite being a fully grown adult Hobbit. Accompanying Treebeard to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entmoot\\\\\\">Entmoot</a>\\\\u00a0and later to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isengard\\\\\\">Isengard</a>, he and Pippin took up residence in an Isengard gate-house. It was here that he first encountered\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Th%C3%A9oden\\\\\\">King Th\\\\u00e9oden</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Rohan</a>, and was reunited with four of the remaining members of the Fellowship.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Merry was separated from Pippin after his friend beheld\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>\\\\u00a0in the\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palant%C3%ADr\\\\\\">palant\\\\u00edr</a></i>\\\\u00a0and was then hastily taken to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>\\\\u00a0with Gandalf on\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shadowfax_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Shadowfax</a>. Merry swore fealty to Th\\\\u00e9oden and became esquire to the king. Against Th\\\\u00e9oden's orders, he rode to Gondor with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89owyn\\\\\\">\\\\u00c9owyn</a>, who was disguised as a common soldier. In the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Pelennor_Fields\\\\\\">Battle of the Pelennor Fields</a>, while the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>\\\\u00a0was preoccupied with \\\\u00c9owyn, Merry stabbed him in the sinew behind his knee with a sword that was made by the D\\\\u00fanedain of Arnor for combat against the Nazg\\\\u00fbl. The Black Captain stumbled from Merry's stroke, and \\\\u00c9owyn seized the moment to strike the Captain's head, destroying him. This fulfilled the prophecy, as he was not killed \\\\\\"by the hand of man,\\\\\\" but rather by a hobbit and a woman. Merry heard Th\\\\u00e9oden's last words, but went unnoticed by the honour escort of Riders; Pippin found him wandering in the city.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>\\\\u00a0healed him and he recovered fully, more quickly than \\\\u00c9owyn.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>For his bravery in battle, Merry was knighted by King\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89omer\\\\\\">\\\\u00c9omer</a>\\\\u00a0as a Knight of the Mark. During the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scouring_of_the_Shire\\\\\\">scouring of the Shire</a>, he led the hobbits in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Bywater\\\\\\">Battle of Bywater</a>, and personally killed the leader of the opposing forces.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-23T07:18:06.380Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 31, "path": "0001000100010008", "content_type": 10, "depth": 4, "slug": "meriadoc-brandybuck", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T21:54:07.074Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/meriadoc-brandybuck/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": true, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "title": "May Thin Kyi", "locked": false}	\N	31	2
234	f	2018-01-20 22:04:14.803964+00	{"host_language_relationship": [], "expired": false, "image": 60, "expire_at": null, "body": "[{\\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Treebeard</b>\\\\u00a0(<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sindarin\\\\\\">Sindarin</a>:\\\\u00a0<i>Fangorn</i>) is a fictional character from\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tolkien%27s_legendarium\\\\\\">fantasy writings</a>. The eldest of the species of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ent\\\\\\">Ents</a>, he is said to live in the ancient\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fangorn\\\\\\">Forest of Fangorn</a>\\\\u00a0and stands fourteen feet (4 m) in height. He is treelike in appearance, with leafy hair and a rigid structure.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0His home of Fangorn Forest lies next to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isengard\\\\\\">Isengard</a>, where\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saruman\\\\\\">Saruman the White</a>\\\\u00a0resides. Treebeard's motto is \\\\\\"Do not be hasty.\\\\\\"<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Two_Towers\\\\\\">The Two Towers</a></i>\\\\u00a0he meets with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>, two\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">Hobbits</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0known also as Merry and Pippin.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0Treebeard is known to have a strong hatred of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Orcs</a>, and, after Saruman's betrayal of the Ents, of Saruman as well.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0During his initial encounter with the two hobbits, he is so agitated that he misidentifies them as orc spies. He then carries them to the white wizard.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Spirits were sent by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eru_Il%C3%BAvatar\\\\\\">Eru Il\\\\u00favatar</a>\\\\u00a0to inhabit the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree\\\\\\">trees</a>, which the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vala_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Vala</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yavanna\\\\\\">Yavanna</a>\\\\u00a0had created along with other plants or\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_plants\\\\\\">olvar</a></i>. The Vala longed for their protection since\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morgoth\\\\\\">Morgoth</a>\\\\u00a0or\\\\u00a0<i>Melkor</i>\\\\u00a0was destroying the trees and olvar, which could not defend themselves from him. The Ents were created by Il\\\\u00favatar at the behest of Yavanna as the\\\\u00a0<i>Shepherds of the Forest</i>\\\\u00a0or\\\\u00a0<i>Tree-herders</i>.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ent#Entwives\\\\\\">Entwives</a>\\\\u00a0were also created for the Ents, but, in the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Age\\\\\\">Second Age</a>, were driven out by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup><sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a></sup><sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Treebeard is the oldest of three remaining original Ents.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0He is said to have once roamed all of the forests in Middle-earth, which included the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mordor\\\\\\">Mordor</a>, and the Blue Mountains. After the loss of the Entwives by the end of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">Third Age</a>, he and the remaining Ents dwelt in the Forest of Fangorn. This led the remaining Ents into isolation and all information from the outside world was cut off.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0The arrival of Merry and Pippin shifted Treebeard's attention to take action against Saruman for hacking down his trees. He led the Ents to war against Saruman and his Orcs. Treebeard later realised that while Saruman had learned much from him, the Wizard had shared no useful information of his own.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"text\\": \\"A large Man-like figure, at least fourteen foot high, very sturdy, with a tall head, and hardly any neck. Whether it was clad in stuff like green and grey bark, or whether that was its hide, was difficult to say. Arms, at a short distance from the trunk, were not wrinkled, but covered with a brown smooth skin. The large feet had seven toes each. Grey beard, deep brown eyes, shot with a green light.\\", \\"attribute_name\\": \\"JRR Tolkien\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Treebeard had been friends with Saruman. It is described in\\\\u00a0<i>The Two Towers</i>\\\\u00a0that Saruman visited Treebeard in Fangorn Forest and had talked with him on various subjects of concern. Saruman gathered information from Treebeard about the Forest of Fangorn; its intertwining paths were of particular concern to him.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After Merry and Pippin's meeting with Treebeard, Treebeard called an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entmoot\\\\\\">Entmoot</a>, which lasted three days, to decide to call an attack on Isengard and Saruman.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Since\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leaflock\\\\\\">Leaflock</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skinbark\\\\\\">Skinbark</a>\\\\u00a0were the oldest of the Ents along with Treebeard, they refused to fight, however, Treebeard thought he was going to his doom during \\\\\\"the last march of the Ents.\\\\\\"<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a>\\\\u00a0Treebeard hoped that some of the younger Ents would come instead of just the two, and, during the night he spread the word. They later launched an assault on Isengard.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TBLOTR-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"https://youtu.be/BbV2Hr0qRdo\\", \\"type\\": \\"embed\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After Treebeard ordered the Ents to march to Isengard, the Ents felled Saruman's walls and destroyed every object in and around Isengard; the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthanc\\\\\\">Tower of Orthanc</a>\\\\u00a0could not be breached, but Saruman was trapped within. Treebeard stopped the attack on the tower when he realised their efforts were in vain; the tower was too strong. The Ents were ordered to unleash the waters of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_rivers#I\\\\\\">River Isen</a>, which flooded Isengard.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-AofAW2-2\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0When Merry and Pippin departed Treebeard he requested them to watch for the Entwives.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treebeard#cite_note-TUCK-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0At one point in the book, Tolkien gives hints on the whereabouts of the Entwives. It is speculated that they were spotted by Samwise Gamgee's cousin Hal in the North Farthing.\\\\u00a0</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-20T22:04:10.634Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 30, "path": "0001000100010007", "content_type": 12, "depth": 4, "slug": "moe-htwe", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T21:49:00.050Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/moe-htwe/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": false, "has_unpublished_changes": true, "title": "Moe Htwe", "lock