bit\\\\\\">hobbit</a>\\\\u00a0in comfortable middle age at 50 years old, was hired despite his objections as a \\\\\\"burglar\\\\\\" by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istari\\\\\\">wizard</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_The_Hobbit_characters#Thorin.27s_company\\\\\\">13 Dwarves</a>\\\\u00a0led by their king\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thorin_Oakenshield\\\\\\">Thorin Oakenshield</a>\\\\u00a0on a quest to reclaim the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lonely_Mountain\\\\\\">Lonely Mountain</a>\\\\u00a0and its treasure from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragon_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">dragon</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smaug\\\\\\">Smaug</a>. The adventure took Bilbo and the companions through the wilderness, to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">elf</a>\\\\u00a0haven of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, across the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>\\\\u00a0and the black forest of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>, to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esgaroth\\\\\\">Lake-town</a>\\\\u00a0in the middle of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Lake_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Long Lake</a>, and eventually to the Mountain itself. Here, after the dragon was killed and the Mountain was reclaimed, soon after that the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Five_Armies\\\\\\">Battle of Five Armies</a>\\\\u00a0took place.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In his journey, Bilbo encountered other fantastic creatures, including\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Troll_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">trolls</a>, elves,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_animals#Great_Spiders\\\\\\">giant spiders</a>, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beorn\\\\\\">man who can change shape into a bear</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">goblins</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eagle_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">eagles</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warg\\\\\\">wolves</a>\\\\u00a0and a slimy, murderous creature named\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gollum\\\\\\">Gollum</a>. Underground, near Gollum's lair, Bilbo accidentally found a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">magic ring of invisibility</a>, which he used to escape from Gollum.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>By the end of the journey, Bilbo had become wiser and more confident, having saved the day in many precarious situations. Bilbo's journey has been compared to a pilgrimage of grace. The Hobbit can be characterized as a \\\\\\"Christian\\\\u00a0<i>bildungsroman</i>\\\\u00a0which equates progress to wisdom gained in the form of a rite of passage.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0He rescued the dwarves from giant spiders with the magic ring and a short\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_weapons_and_armour#Sting\\\\\\">Elven-sword</a>\\\\u00a0he acquired. He used the ring to sneak around in dangerous places, as well as his wits to smuggle the dwarves out of the elves' prisons. When tensions arose over ownership of the recovered treasure, he tried unsuccessfully to bring the opposing sides to compromise, using the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Arkenstone\\\\\\">Arkenstone</a>, a stolen heirloom jewel, as leverage. This strained his relationship with Thorin, but the two were reconciled at Thorin's deathbed. At the end of the story, Bilbo returned to his home in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0only to find that several of his relatives, believing him to be dead, were trying to claim his home and possessions. In addition to becoming wealthy from his share of the dwarves' treasure, he found that he, like\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adam\\\\\\">Adam</a>, had traded respectability for experience and wisdom. At the end, Gandalf proclaims Bilbo is no longer the Hobbit he was. This is certainly true as Bilbo has fully matured. Continuing the pilgrimage theme, a true pilgrimage does not end at the destination, but rather when the wanderer is absolved, blessed, and ready to return home.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Lord of the Rings\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p><i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">The Fellowship of the Ring</a></i>, the first volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, begins with Bilbo's \\\\\\"eleventy-first\\\\\\" (111th) birthday, 60 years after the beginning of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. The main character of the novel is\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>, Bilbo's cousin,<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[nb 1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0who celebrates his 33rd birthday and legally comes of age on the same day.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a02989 (<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_Reckoning\\\\\\">S.R.</a>\\\\u00a01389), Bilbo, a lifelong bachelor, adopted Frodo, the orphaned son of his first cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primula_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Primula Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and his second cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drogo_Baggins\\\\\\">Drogo Baggins</a>, and made him his heir. Though Frodo was actually \\\\\\"his first\\\\u00a0<i>and</i>\\\\u00a0second\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cousin#Cousin_chart\\\\\\">cousin once removed</a>\\\\u00a0either way\\\\\\",<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0the two regarded each other as uncle and nephew.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>All this time Bilbo had kept his magic ring, with no idea of its significance, using it mostly to hide from his obnoxious cousins, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sackville-Baggins\\\\\\">Sackville-Bagginses</a>, when they came to visit.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>'s investigations revealed it to be the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0forged by the Dark Lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>. The Ring had prolonged Bilbo's life beyond the normal hobbit span, and at 111 he still looked 50. While the Ring did not initially corrupt him as it had its previous owners, it was beginning to affect him; over the years, it had begun to prey on his mind when out of his sight, and he lost sleep and felt \\\\\\"thin, sort of\\\\u00a0<i>stretched</i>\\\\u00a0\\\\u2026 like butter that has been scraped over too much bread\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>On the night of his and Frodo's birthday, Bilbo threw himself a party and invited all of the Shire. He signed his home,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>, and estate over to Frodo. He then gave a farewell address to his neighbors, at the end of which he put on the Ring and vanished from sight. As Bilbo prepared finally to leave the house, he reacted with panic and suspicion when Gandalf tried to persuade him to leave the Ring with Frodo. Bilbo refused to give up the Ring, referring to it as his \\\\\\"precious\\\\\\" \\\\u2013 just as Gollum had. Gandalf lost his temper with his old friend and talked some sense into him. Bilbo admitted he would have liked to be rid of the Ring, and he left it behind, becoming the first person to do so voluntarily. He left the Shire that night, and was never seen in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbiton\\\\\\">Hobbiton</a>\\\\u00a0again.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>His earlier adventure, his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eccentric_(behavior)\\\\\\">eccentric</a>\\\\u00a0habits as a hobbit, and his sudden disappearance led to the enduring figure of \\\\\\"Mad Baggins\\\\\\" in hobbit folklore, who disappeared with a flash and a bang and returned with gold and jewels.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Freed of the Ring's power over his senses, Bilbo travelled first to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, and then on to visit the dwarves of the Lonely Mountain. After he returned to Rivendell he spent much of the next 17 years living a pleasant life of retirement: eating, sleeping, writing poetry, and working on his memoirs,\\\\u00a0<i>There and Back Again</i>, known as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. He became a scholar of Elven lore, leaving behind the\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_languages_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elvish</a></i>, which forms the basis of what is known to us as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Silmarillion\\\\\\">The Silmarillion</a></i>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>When Frodo and his friends\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Samwise Gamgee</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>\\\\u00a0stopped in Rivendell on their quest to destroy the Ring, Bilbo was still alive but now visibly aged, the years having caught up with him after he surrendered the Ring. Upon seeing the Ring again, he suddenly tried to take it from Frodo; he returned to his senses when a terrified Frodo backed away, and he broke down in tears, apologizing for bringing the burden of the Ring onto Frodo.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After the quest to destroy the Ring was fulfilled in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>, Gandalf and the four Hobbits visited Rivendell on their way back to the Shire and found Bilbo still living there. He gave Frodo a set of manuscripts that later became\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the Elvish</i>, and also gave Sam a small bag of gold that represented the last of his share from Smaug's vast hoard. Two years later Bilbo accompanied Gandalf,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>, and Frodo to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grey_Havens\\\\\\">Grey Havens</a>, there to take ship for\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tol_Eress%C3%ABa\\\\\\">Tol Eress\\\\u00eba</a>\\\\u00a0across the sea, on 29th 'September'\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a03021. He had already celebrated his 131st birthday by this time, surpassing the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Took\\\\\\">Old Took</a>\\\\u00a0by one year and becoming the oldest Hobbit ever in Middle-earth. (The natural lifespan of Hobbits is about 100 years.)<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-4\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-20T21:55:36.980Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 38, "path": "000100010001000F", "content_type": 12, "depth": 4, "slug": "tun", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:23:37.638Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/tun/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": false, "has_unpublished_changes": true, "title": "Than Tun", "locked": false}	\N	38	2
222	f	2018-01-20 21:55:36.980735+00	{"host_language_relationship": [], "expired": false, "image": 56, "expire_at": null, "body": "[{\\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Bilbo Baggins</b>\\\\u00a0is the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Title_character\\\\\\">title character</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protagonist\\\\\\">protagonist</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a>'s 1937 novel\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>, as well as a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supporting_character\\\\\\">supporting character</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>. In Tolkien's narrative\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conceit\\\\\\">conceit</a>, in which all the writings of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>\\\\u00a0are translations from the fictitious volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Book_of_Westmarch\\\\\\">Red Book of Westmarch</a></i>, Bilbo is the author of\\\\u00a0<i>The Hobbit</i>\\\\u00a0and translator of various \\\\\\"works from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_language\\\\\\">elvish</a>\\\\\\" (as mentioned in the end of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>).</p><p></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Hobbit\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"caption\\": \\"Bilbo Baggins illustration\\", \\"style\\": \\"half\\", \\"image\\": 28}, \\"type\\": \\"image\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<i>The Hobbit</i>, Bilbo Baggins, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">hobbit</a>\\\\u00a0in comfortable middle age at 50 years old, was hired despite his objections as a \\\\\\"burglar\\\\\\" by the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istari\\\\\\">wizard</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_The_Hobbit_characters#Thorin.27s_company\\\\\\">13 Dwarves</a>\\\\u00a0led by their king\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thorin_Oakenshield\\\\\\">Thorin Oakenshield</a>\\\\u00a0on a quest to reclaim the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lonely_Mountain\\\\\\">Lonely Mountain</a>\\\\u00a0and its treasure from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragon_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">dragon</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smaug\\\\\\">Smaug</a>. The adventure took Bilbo and the companions through the wilderness, to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">elf</a>\\\\u00a0haven of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, across the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>\\\\u00a0and the black forest of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>, to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esgaroth\\\\\\">Lake-town</a>\\\\u00a0in the middle of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Lake_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Long Lake</a>, and eventually to the Mountain itself. Here, after the dragon was killed and the Mountain was reclaimed, soon after that the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Five_Armies\\\\\\">Battle of Five Armies</a>\\\\u00a0took place.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In his journey, Bilbo encountered other fantastic creatures, including\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Troll_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">trolls</a>, elves,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_animals#Great_Spiders\\\\\\">giant spiders</a>, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beorn\\\\\\">man who can change shape into a bear</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">goblins</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eagle_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">eagles</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warg\\\\\\">wolves</a>\\\\u00a0and a slimy, murderous creature named\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gollum\\\\\\">Gollum</a>. Underground, near Gollum's lair, Bilbo accidentally found a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">magic ring of invisibility</a>, which he used to escape from Gollum.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>By the end of the journey, Bilbo had become wiser and more confident, having saved the day in many precarious situations. Bilbo's journey has been compared to a pilgrimage of grace. The Hobbit can be characterized as a \\\\\\"Christian\\\\u00a0<i>bildungsroman</i>\\\\u00a0which equates progress to wisdom gained in the form of a rite of passage.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a>\\\\u00a0He rescued the dwarves from giant spiders with the magic ring and a short\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_weapons_and_armour#Sting\\\\\\">Elven-sword</a>\\\\u00a0he acquired. He used the ring to sneak around in dangerous places, as well as his wits to smuggle the dwarves out of the elves' prisons. When tensions arose over ownership of the recovered treasure, he tried unsuccessfully to bring the opposing sides to compromise, using the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Arkenstone\\\\\\">Arkenstone</a>, a stolen heirloom jewel, as leverage. This strained his relationship with Thorin, but the two were reconciled at Thorin's deathbed. At the end of the story, Bilbo returned to his home in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0only to find that several of his relatives, believing him to be dead, were trying to claim his home and possessions. In addition to becoming wealthy from his share of the dwarves' treasure, he found that he, like\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adam\\\\\\">Adam</a>, had traded respectability for experience and wisdom. At the end, Gandalf proclaims Bilbo is no longer the Hobbit he was. This is certainly true as Bilbo has fully matured. Continuing the pilgrimage theme, a true pilgrimage does not end at the destination, but rather when the wanderer is absolved, blessed, and ready to return home.<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-Saint_Benedict_Press-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Lord of the Rings\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p><i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Fellowship_of_the_Ring\\\\\\">The Fellowship of the Ring</a></i>, the first volume of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>, begins with Bilbo's \\\\\\"eleventy-first\\\\\\" (111th) birthday, 60 years after the beginning of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. The main character of the novel is\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\\\\\\">Frodo Baggins</a>, Bilbo's cousin,<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[nb 1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0who celebrates his 33rd birthday and legally comes of age on the same day.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a02989 (<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_Reckoning\\\\\\">S.R.</a>\\\\u00a01389), Bilbo, a lifelong bachelor, adopted Frodo, the orphaned son of his first cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primula_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Primula Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and his second cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drogo_Baggins\\\\\\">Drogo Baggins</a>, and made him his heir. Though Frodo was actually \\\\\\"his first\\\\u00a0<i>and</i>\\\\u00a0second\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cousin#Cousin_chart\\\\\\">cousin once removed</a>\\\\u00a0either way\\\\\\",<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a>\\\\u00a0the two regarded each other as uncle and nephew.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>All this time Bilbo had kept his magic ring, with no idea of its significance, using it mostly to hide from his obnoxious cousins, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sackville-Baggins\\\\\\">Sackville-Bagginses</a>, when they came to visit.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>'s investigations revealed it to be the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0forged by the Dark Lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>. The Ring had prolonged Bilbo's life beyond the normal hobbit span, and at 111 he still looked 50. While the Ring did not initially corrupt him as it had its previous owners, it was beginning to affect him; over the years, it had begun to prey on his mind when out of his sight, and he lost sleep and felt \\\\\\"thin, sort of\\\\u00a0<i>stretched</i>\\\\u00a0\\\\u2026 like butter that has been scraped over too much bread\\\\\\".<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-LotR_party-3\\\\\\">[2]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>On the night of his and Frodo's birthday, Bilbo threw himself a party and invited all of the Shire. He signed his home,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>, and estate over to Frodo. He then gave a farewell address to his neighbors, at the end of which he put on the Ring and vanished from sight. As Bilbo prepared finally to leave the house, he reacted with panic and suspicion when Gandalf tried to persuade him to leave the Ring with Frodo. Bilbo refused to give up the Ring, referring to it as his \\\\\\"precious\\\\\\" \\\\u2013 just as Gollum had. Gandalf lost his temper with his old friend and talked some sense into him. Bilbo admitted he would have liked to be rid of the Ring, and he left it behind, becoming the first person to do so voluntarily. He left the Shire that night, and was never seen in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbiton\\\\\\">Hobbiton</a>\\\\u00a0again.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>His earlier adventure, his\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eccentric_(behavior)\\\\\\">eccentric</a>\\\\u00a0habits as a hobbit, and his sudden disappearance led to the enduring figure of \\\\\\"Mad Baggins\\\\\\" in hobbit folklore, who disappeared with a flash and a bang and returned with gold and jewels.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Freed of the Ring's power over his senses, Bilbo travelled first to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, and then on to visit the dwarves of the Lonely Mountain. After he returned to Rivendell he spent much of the next 17 years living a pleasant life of retirement: eating, sleeping, writing poetry, and working on his memoirs,\\\\u00a0<i>There and Back Again</i>, known as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>. He became a scholar of Elven lore, leaving behind the\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvish_languages_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elvish</a></i>, which forms the basis of what is known to us as\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Silmarillion\\\\\\">The Silmarillion</a></i>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>When Frodo and his friends\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Samwise Gamgee</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>\\\\u00a0stopped in Rivendell on their quest to destroy the Ring, Bilbo was still alive but now visibly aged, the years having caught up with him after he surrendered the Ring. Upon seeing the Ring again, he suddenly tried to take it from Frodo; he returned to his senses when a terrified Frodo backed away, and he broke down in tears, apologizing for bringing the burden of the Ring onto Frodo.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>After the quest to destroy the Ring was fulfilled in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Return_of_the_King\\\\\\">The Return of the King</a></i>, Gandalf and the four Hobbits visited Rivendell on their way back to the Shire and found Bilbo still living there. He gave Frodo a set of manuscripts that later became\\\\u00a0<i>Translations from the Elvish</i>, and also gave Sam a small bag of gold that represented the last of his share from Smaug's vast hoard. Two years later Bilbo accompanied Gandalf,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>,\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>, and Frodo to the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grey_Havens\\\\\\">Grey Havens</a>, there to take ship for\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tol_Eress%C3%ABa\\\\\\">Tol Eress\\\\u00eba</a>\\\\u00a0across the sea, on 29th 'September'\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_Age\\\\\\">T.A.</a>\\\\u00a03021. He had already celebrated his 131st birthday by this time, surpassing the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Took\\\\\\">Old Took</a>\\\\u00a0by one year and becoming the oldest Hobbit ever in Middle-earth. (The natural lifespan of Hobbits is about 100 years.)<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins#cite_note-4\\\\\\">[3]</a></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-04-26T03:09:25.133Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 38, "path": "000100010001000F", "content_type": 12, "depth": 4, "slug": "tun", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:23:37.638Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/bilbo/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": false, "has_unpublished_changes": true, "title": "Than Tun", "locked": false}	\N	38	2
227	f	2018-01-20 21:57:24.276697+00	{"host_language_relationship": [], "expired": false, "image": 56, "expire_at": null, "body": "[{\\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Frodo Baggins</b>\\\\u00a0is a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Character_(arts)\\\\\\">fictional character</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tolkien%27s_legendarium\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien's legendarium</a>, and the main protagonist of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>. Frodo is a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">hobbit</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0who inherits the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0from his cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins\\\\\\">Bilbo Baggins</a>\\\\u00a0and undertakes the quest to destroy it in the fires of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Doom\\\\\\">Mount Doom</a>. He is also mentioned in Tolkien's posthumously published works,\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Silmarillion\\\\\\">The Silmarillion</a></i>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unfinished_Tales\\\\\\">Unfinished Tales</a></i>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"Concept and creation\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Frodo did not appear until the third draft of\\\\u00a0<i>A Long-Expected Party</i>\\\\u00a0(the first chapter of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>), when he was named Bingo (after a family of toy\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koala\\\\\\">koala</a>\\\\u00a0owned by Tolkien's children), son of Bilbo Baggins and Primula Brandybuck.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins#cite_note-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0In the fourth draft, he was renamed Bingo Bolger-Baggins, son of Rollo Bolger and Primula Brandybuck.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[2]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0Tolkien did not change the name to Frodo until the third phase of writing, when much of the narrative, as far as the hobbits' arrival in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, had already taken shape.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins#cite_note-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0Prior to this, the name \\\\\\"Frodo\\\\\\" had been used for the character who eventually became\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins#cite_note-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Fellowship of the Ring\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p><i>The Fellowship of the Ring</i>\\\\u00a0opens as Frodo came of age (at 33 years old) and Bilbo left\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0for good on his one hundred and eleventh birthday. Frodo inherited\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">Bilbo's ring</a>, which were both introduced in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>, at this time, was not certain about the origin of the Ring, so he warned Frodo to avoid using it and to keep it secret. Frodo kept the Ring hidden for 17 years, resulting in it giving him the same longevity of Bilbo, until Gandalf returned to tell him that it was the One Ring of the Dark Lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>, who desired to use it to conquer\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Realizing that he was a danger to the Shire as long as he remained there with the Ring, Frodo decided to leave home and take the Ring to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, home of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>, a mighty\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elf</a>\\\\u00a0lord. He left the Shire with three companions: his gardener\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Samwise Gamgee</a>\\\\u00a0and his cousins\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>. They escaped just in time, for Sauron's most powerful servants, the Nine\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>, had entered the Shire as Black Riders, looking for Bilbo and the Ring. They followed Frodo's trail across the Shire and nearly intercepted him.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Frodo and his companions escaped the Black Riders by travelling through the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Forest\\\\\\">Old Forest</a>, but they were misled by the magic of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Man_Willow\\\\\\">Old Man Willow</a>\\\\u00a0until they were rescued by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Bombadil\\\\\\">Tom Bombadil</a>, who gave them shelter and guided them on their way. After leaving Bombadil, they were caught in fog on the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow_Downs\\\\\\">Barrow Downs</a>\\\\u00a0by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow-wight\\\\\\">Barrow-wights</a>\\\\u00a0and were entranced under a spell. Frodo broke loose from the spell, attacked the barrow-wight and summoned Tom Bombadil, who again rescued the hobbits and set them on their way.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>At the\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prancing_Pony\\\\\\">Prancing Pony</a></i>, an inn in the village of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bree_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Bree</a>, Frodo received a delayed\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Gandalf.27s_letter\\\\\\">letter from Gandalf</a>, and met\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>, also called Strider, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranger_of_the_North\\\\\\">Ranger of the North</a>. Strider became the hobbits' guide while journeying through the wilderness towards Rivendell. The One Ring slipped onto Frodo's finger inadvertently in the\\\\u00a0<i>Prancing Pony'</i>s common room, turning Frodo invisible. This attracted the attention of Sauron's agents, who ransacked the hobbits' rooms in the night. The group, under Aragorn's guidance, quickly fled through the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minor_places_in_Middle-earth#Midgewater_Marshes\\\\\\">Midgewater Marshes</a>\\\\u00a0and again escaped the Nazg\\\\u00fbl.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>While encamped at\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amon_S%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Amon S\\\\u00fbl</a>, they were found and attacked by five Nazg\\\\u00fbl. The chief of the Nazg\\\\u00fbl, known as the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>, stabbed Frodo with a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morgul-blade\\\\\\">Morgul-blade</a>, before Aragorn routed all five of them with fire. A piece of this blade remained in Frodo's shoulder and, working its way towards his heart, threatened to turn him into a wraith under the control of the Witch-king. With the help of his companions and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glorfindel\\\\\\">Glorfindel</a>, Frodo was able to evade the remaining Ringwraiths and reach Rivendell. Although almost overcome by his wound, once there he was healed over time by Elrond; it was said and later seen that the wound would never completely heal, however, as it was as much spiritual as physical.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In Rivendell, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Elrond\\\\\\">Council of Elrond</a>\\\\u00a0met and resolved to destroy the Ring by casting it into\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Doom\\\\\\">Mount Doom</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mordor\\\\\\">Mordor</a>, the realm of Sauron. Frodo, realizing that he was destined for this task, stepped forward to be the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ring-bearer\\\\\\">Ring-bearer</a>. A\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship of nine companions</a>\\\\u00a0was formed to guide and protect him: the hobbits, Gandalf, Aragorn, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dwarf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">dwarf</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimli_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Gimli</a>, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">elf</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legolas\\\\\\">Legolas</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>, and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boromir\\\\\\">Boromir</a>, a man of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>. Together they set out from Rivendell. Frodo was armed with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sting_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Sting</a>, Bilbo's Elvish knife, and wore Bilbo's coat of Dwarven mail made of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mithril\\\\\\">mithril</a></i>. The company, seeking a way over the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>, first tried the Pass of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caradhras\\\\\\">Caradhras</a>, but abandoned it in favour of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moria_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">mines of Moria</a>. In Moria Frodo was stabbed by an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Orc</a>-spear, but his coat of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mithril\\\\\\">mithril</a></i>\\\\u00a0armour saved his life. They were led through the mines by Gandalf, until he fell battling a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balrog\\\\\\">Balrog</a>, and then by Aragorn to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lothl%C3%B3rien\\\\\\">Lothl\\\\u00f3rien</a>. There\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>, the Lady of the Woods, gave Frodo an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Elven-cloaks\\\\\\">Elven cloak</a>\\\\u00a0and a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phial_of_Galadriel\\\\\\">phial</a>\\\\u00a0carrying the Light of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E%C3%A4rendil\\\\\\">E\\\\u00e4rendil</a>\\\\u00a0to aid him on his dangerous quest.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Having then travelled some miles down the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anduin\\\\\\">Anduin</a>\\\\u00a0by boat, the Fellowship reached\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parth_Galen\\\\\\">Parth Galen</a>. There, Boromir, having fallen to the lure of the Ring, tried to take it by force from Frodo. Frodo escaped by putting on the Ring and becoming invisible. This event broke the Fellowship; Boromir was later slain defending Merry and Pippin from invading Orcs, who captured the two hobbits. Aragorn, Gimli and Legolas gave him a hero's funeral before setting out after the two hobbits. Frodo chose to continue the quest alone, but Sam followed his master, joining him on the journey to Mordor.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-12T22:10:53.935Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 35, "path": "000100010001000C", "content_type": 10, "depth": 4, "slug": "frodo", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:10:53.993Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/frodo/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": true, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "title": "Than Tun", "locked": false}	\N	35	2
228	f	2018-01-20 21:57:31.686675+00	{"host_language_relationship": [], "expired": false, "image": 56, "expire_at": null, "body": "[{\\"value\\": \\"<p><b>Frodo Baggins</b>\\\\u00a0is a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Character_(arts)\\\\\\">fictional character</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tolkien%27s_legendarium\\\\\\">J. R. R. Tolkien's legendarium</a>, and the main protagonist of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings\\\\\\">The Lord of the Rings</a></i>. Frodo is a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbit\\\\\\">hobbit</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0who inherits the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">One Ring</a>\\\\u00a0from his cousin\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins\\\\\\">Bilbo Baggins</a>\\\\u00a0and undertakes the quest to destroy it in the fires of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Doom\\\\\\">Mount Doom</a>. He is also mentioned in Tolkien's posthumously published works,\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Silmarillion\\\\\\">The Silmarillion</a></i>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unfinished_Tales\\\\\\">Unfinished Tales</a></i>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"Concept and creation\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Frodo did not appear until the third draft of\\\\u00a0<i>A Long-Expected Party</i>\\\\u00a0(the first chapter of\\\\u00a0<i>The Lord of the Rings</i>), when he was named Bingo (after a family of toy\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koala\\\\\\">koala</a>\\\\u00a0owned by Tolkien's children), son of Bilbo Baggins and Primula Brandybuck.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins#cite_note-1\\\\\\">[1]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0In the fourth draft, he was renamed Bingo Bolger-Baggins, son of Rollo Bolger and Primula Brandybuck.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins#cite_note-2\\\\\\">[2]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0Tolkien did not change the name to Frodo until the third phase of writing, when much of the narrative, as far as the hobbits' arrival in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, had already taken shape.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins#cite_note-3\\\\\\">[3]</a></sup>\\\\u00a0Prior to this, the name \\\\\\"Frodo\\\\\\" had been used for the character who eventually became\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>.<sup><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins#cite_note-4\\\\\\">[4]</a></sup></p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": {\\"size\\": \\"h2\\", \\"header_text\\": \\"The Fellowship of the Ring\\"}, \\"type\\": \\"header\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p><i>The Fellowship of the Ring</i>\\\\u00a0opens as Frodo came of age (at 33 years old) and Bilbo left\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">the Shire</a>\\\\u00a0for good on his one hundred and eleventh birthday. Frodo inherited\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bag_End\\\\\\">Bag End</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\\\\\\">Bilbo's ring</a>, which were both introduced in\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hobbit\\\\\\">The Hobbit</a></i>.\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\\\\\\">Gandalf</a>, at this time, was not certain about the origin of the Ring, so he warned Frodo to avoid using it and to keep it secret. Frodo kept the Ring hidden for 17 years, resulting in it giving him the same longevity of Bilbo, until Gandalf returned to tell him that it was the One Ring of the Dark Lord\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\\\\\\">Sauron</a>, who desired to use it to conquer\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-earth\\\\\\">Middle-earth</a>.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Realizing that he was a danger to the Shire as long as he remained there with the Ring, Frodo decided to leave home and take the Ring to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\\\\\\">Rivendell</a>, home of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\\\\\\">Elrond</a>, a mighty\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Elf</a>\\\\u00a0lord. He left the Shire with three companions: his gardener\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\\\\\\">Samwise Gamgee</a>\\\\u00a0and his cousins\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\\\\\\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>\\\\u00a0and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\\\\\\">Peregrin Took</a>. They escaped just in time, for Sauron's most powerful servants, the Nine\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazg%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Nazg\\\\u00fbl</a>, had entered the Shire as Black Riders, looking for Bilbo and the Ring. They followed Frodo's trail across the Shire and nearly intercepted him.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Frodo and his companions escaped the Black Riders by travelling through the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Forest\\\\\\">Old Forest</a>, but they were misled by the magic of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Man_Willow\\\\\\">Old Man Willow</a>\\\\u00a0until they were rescued by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Bombadil\\\\\\">Tom Bombadil</a>, who gave them shelter and guided them on their way. After leaving Bombadil, they were caught in fog on the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow_Downs\\\\\\">Barrow Downs</a>\\\\u00a0by\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrow-wight\\\\\\">Barrow-wights</a>\\\\u00a0and were entranced under a spell. Frodo broke loose from the spell, attacked the barrow-wight and summoned Tom Bombadil, who again rescued the hobbits and set them on their way.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>At the\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prancing_Pony\\\\\\">Prancing Pony</a></i>, an inn in the village of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bree_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Bree</a>, Frodo received a delayed\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Gandalf.27s_letter\\\\\\">letter from Gandalf</a>, and met\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\\\\\\">Aragorn</a>, also called Strider, a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranger_of_the_North\\\\\\">Ranger of the North</a>. Strider became the hobbits' guide while journeying through the wilderness towards Rivendell. The One Ring slipped onto Frodo's finger inadvertently in the\\\\u00a0<i>Prancing Pony'</i>s common room, turning Frodo invisible. This attracted the attention of Sauron's agents, who ransacked the hobbits' rooms in the night. The group, under Aragorn's guidance, quickly fled through the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minor_places_in_Middle-earth#Midgewater_Marshes\\\\\\">Midgewater Marshes</a>\\\\u00a0and again escaped the Nazg\\\\u00fbl.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>While encamped at\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amon_S%C3%BBl\\\\\\">Amon S\\\\u00fbl</a>, they were found and attacked by five Nazg\\\\u00fbl. The chief of the Nazg\\\\u00fbl, known as the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-king_of_Angmar\\\\\\">Witch-king of Angmar</a>, stabbed Frodo with a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morgul-blade\\\\\\">Morgul-blade</a>, before Aragorn routed all five of them with fire. A piece of this blade remained in Frodo's shoulder and, working its way towards his heart, threatened to turn him into a wraith under the control of the Witch-king. With the help of his companions and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glorfindel\\\\\\">Glorfindel</a>, Frodo was able to evade the remaining Ringwraiths and reach Rivendell. Although almost overcome by his wound, once there he was healed over time by Elrond; it was said and later seen that the wound would never completely heal, however, as it was as much spiritual as physical.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>In Rivendell, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Elrond\\\\\\">Council of Elrond</a>\\\\u00a0met and resolved to destroy the Ring by casting it into\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Doom\\\\\\">Mount Doom</a>\\\\u00a0in\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mordor\\\\\\">Mordor</a>, the realm of Sauron. Frodo, realizing that he was destined for this task, stepped forward to be the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ring-bearer\\\\\\">Ring-bearer</a>. A\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\\\\\\">Fellowship of nine companions</a>\\\\u00a0was formed to guide and protect him: the hobbits, Gandalf, Aragorn, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dwarf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">dwarf</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimli_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Gimli</a>, the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">elf</a>\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legolas\\\\\\">Legolas</a>\\\\u00a0of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirkwood\\\\\\">Mirkwood</a>, and\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boromir\\\\\\">Boromir</a>, a man of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\\\\\\">Gondor</a>. Together they set out from Rivendell. Frodo was armed with\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sting_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Sting</a>, Bilbo's Elvish knife, and wore Bilbo's coat of Dwarven mail made of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mithril\\\\\\">mithril</a></i>. The company, seeking a way over the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\\\\\\">Misty Mountains</a>, first tried the Pass of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caradhras\\\\\\">Caradhras</a>, but abandoned it in favour of the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moria_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">mines of Moria</a>. In Moria Frodo was stabbed by an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\\\\\\">Orc</a>-spear, but his coat of\\\\u00a0<i><a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mithril\\\\\\">mithril</a></i>\\\\u00a0armour saved his life. They were led through the mines by Gandalf, until he fell battling a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balrog\\\\\\">Balrog</a>, and then by Aragorn to\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lothl%C3%B3rien\\\\\\">Lothl\\\\u00f3rien</a>. There\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\\\\\\">Galadriel</a>, the Lady of the Woods, gave Frodo an\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_objects#Elven-cloaks\\\\\\">Elven cloak</a>\\\\u00a0and a\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phial_of_Galadriel\\\\\\">phial</a>\\\\u00a0carrying the Light of\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E%C3%A4rendil\\\\\\">E\\\\u00e4rendil</a>\\\\u00a0to aid him on his dangerous quest.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}, {\\"value\\": \\"<p>Having then travelled some miles down the\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anduin\\\\\\">Anduin</a>\\\\u00a0by boat, the Fellowship reached\\\\u00a0<a href=\\\\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parth_Galen\\\\\\">Parth Galen</a>. There, Boromir, having fallen to the lure of the Ring, tried to take it by force from Frodo. Frodo escaped by putting on the Ring and becoming invisible. This event broke the Fellowship; Boromir was later slain defending Merry and Pippin from invading Orcs, who captured the two hobbits. Aragorn, Gimli and Legolas gave him a hero's funeral before setting out after the two hobbits. Frodo chose to continue the quest alone, but Sam followed his master, joining him on the journey to Mordor.</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-20T21:57:24.276Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 35, "path": "000100010001000C", "content_type": 10, "depth": 4, "slug": "frodo", "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:10:53.993Z", "numchild": 0, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/frodo/", "seo_title": "", "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "show_in_menus": false, "live": true, "has_unpublished_changes": true, "title": "Than Tun", "locked": false}	\N	35	2
