 meters) above the plain of Isengard, and ended in four sharp peaks. Its only entrance was at the top of a high stair, and above that was a small window and balcony.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\", \\"value\\": {\\"attribute_name\\": \\"Saruman\\", \\"text\\": \\"Against the power of Mordor there can be no victory\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"White wizard\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Orthanc housed one of the palant\\\\u00edri of the South Kingdom, and was guarded by a special warden. In the days of the early Stewards the tower was locked and its keys taken to Minas Tirith. When Isengard fell to the Dunlendings in T.A. 2710 they were unable to enter the tower.</p>\\"}]", "path": "0001000100030003", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-23T07:52:58.808Z", "image": 8, "title": "Isengard", "show_in_menus": false, "locked": false, "expire_at": null, "seo_title": "", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T19:45:42.890Z", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "depth": 4, "owner": 1, "slug": "isengard", "search_description": ""}	\N	14	1
284	f	2018-01-25 04:39:53.447652+00	{"path": "000100010001000B", "go_live_at": null, "content_type": 10, "depth": 4, "show_in_menus": false, "image": 58, "host_language_relationship": [], "numchild": 0, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T22:07:10.326Z", "seo_title": "", "search_description": "", "live": true, "email_address": "yan.pye.aung@gmail.com", "slug": "pergrin-took", "expired": false, "title": "May May Thi", "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>I am May, I was raised in the Mekong Delta. I first worked as a social worker and then after university he became an English teacher. After growing up, working throughout the Mekong Delta, I decided to become a tour guide. Since 2009, I has been a freelance biking tour guide all over Myanmar for different tour companies. I understands the country, people and their customs. This allows me to take visitors into the countryside to meet local people and experience the real rural life.</p><p>As a child of the countryside I can easily help guests get closer with local people, their culture and way of life,...through biking. Everyone falls in love with the places that I leads them to.</p><p></p>\\"}]", "expire_at": null, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-25T04:30:31.900Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 34, "url_path": "/homepage/hosts/pergrin-took/", "locked": false}	\N	34	1
95	f	2017-01-23 07:53:44.276+00	{"pk": 14, "url_path": "/homepage/place-index-page/isengard/", "go_live_at": null, "live": true, "content_type": 6, "numchild": 0, "expired": false, "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"image\\", \\"value\\": {\\"caption\\": \\"A shield displaying the White Hand of Isengard\\", \\"style\\": \\"half\\", \\"image\\": 7}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>In J. R. R. Tolkien's fictional universe of Middle-earth, Isengard ([\\\\u02c8a\\\\u026a\\\\u02d0.z\\\\u025bn.\\\\u0261\\\\u0251rd]), a translation of the Sindarin Angrenost, was a large fortress. Both names mean \\\\\\"Iron fortress\\\\\\" (cf. German Eisen and Old English is\\\\u00e6rn = iron),[1] though Isengard has a second meaning of \\\\\\"West Guard\\\\\\".</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Armour and emblems\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>The Orcs of Isengard bore upon their shields a White Hand on a black field, and on their helmets an S-rune (&lt;) to signify Saruman. A carved and painted White Hand of stone was set on a black pillar outside the gates of Isengard.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"header\\", \\"value\\": {\\"header_text\\": \\"Orthanc\\", \\"size\\": \\"h2\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Orthanc is the black tower of Isengard. Its name means both \\\\\\"Mount Fang\\\\\\" in Sindarin, and \\\\\\"Cunning Mind\\\\\\" in Old English, the language Tolkien uses to \\\\\\"translate\\\\\\" Rohirric.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Orthanc was, according to J. R. R. Tolkien's legendarium, built during the end of the Second Age by men of Gondor out of four many-sided columns of rock joined together by an unknown process and then hardened. No known weapon could harm it. Although the Ents could split ordinary stone with ease, their assault on the tower only left a few scratches and chips on its surface. Orthanc rose up to more than 500 feet (150 meters) above the plain of Isengard, and ended in four sharp peaks. Its only entrance was at the top of a high stair, and above that was a small window and balcony.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Orthanc housed one of the palant\\\\u00edri of the South Kingdom, and was guarded by a special warden. In the days of the early Stewards the tower was locked and its keys taken to Minas Tirith. When Isengard fell to the Dunlendings in T.A. 2710 they were unable to enter the tower.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"blockquote\\", \\"value\\": {\\"attribute_name\\": \\"Saruman\\", \\"text\\": \\"Against the power of Mordor there can be no victory\\", \\"attribute_group\\": \\"White wizard\\"}}]", "path": "0001000100030003", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-01-23T07:53:29.545Z", "image": 8, "title": "Isengard", "show_in_menus": false, "locked": false, "expire_at": null, "seo_title": "", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T19:45:42.890Z", "has_unpublished_changes": false, "depth": 4, "owner": 1, "slug": "isengard", "search_description": ""}	\N	14	1
