111	f	2017-04-20 03:03:38.802+00	{"locked": false, "go_live_at": null, "owner": 1, "live": true, "url_path": "/homepage/experience-index/singing/", "seo_title": "", "search_description": "", "image": 23, "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-04-16T00:46:42.418Z", "expired": false, "numchild": 0, "pk": 22, "content_type": 14, "depth": 4, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "expire_at": null, "body": "[{\\"value\\": \\"<p>Once the Puerto Rican barrio of Miami, Wynwood is now known as the largest street art gallery in the world! Made famous by the yearly Art Basel art fair, the Wynwood area has exploded into one of the hippest neighborhoods in the country. From wheat pastes to murals, stencils to stickers, every inch of the neighborhood is covered in art. This walking tour of the neighborhood will include information about the street art coupled with the history of the neighborhood, the ins-and-outs of the current changes, and the way that Wynwood fits into the overall picture of Miami. I can give tours in both English and Spanish, and I can arrange for bike rentals for an additional fee. Come and check out Maimi's street art hub!</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T20:40:48.414Z", "slug": "singing", "title": "Street Art Tour", "show_in_menus": false, "path": "0001000100020005"}	\N	22	1
307	f	2018-01-27 14:08:45.442685+00	{"depth": 4, "host": 28, "body": "[{\\"value\\": \\"<p>Once the Kingdom, Mandalay is now known as the largest street art gallery in the Myanmar! Made famous by the yearly art fair, the Mandalay area has exploded into one of the hippest neighborhoods in the country. From wheat pastes to murals, stencils to stickers, every inch of the neighborhood is covered in art. This walking tour of the neighborhood will include information about the street art coupled with the history of the neighborhood, the ins-and-outs of the current changes, and the way that Mandalay fits into the overall picture of Myanmar. I can give tours in both English and French, and I can arrange for bike rentals for an additional fee. Come and check out Mandalay's street art hub!</p>\\", \\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\"}]", "url_path": "/homepage/experiences/street-art/", "expired": false, "pk": 22, "owner": 1, "locked": false, "title": "Street Art Tour", "search_description": "", "live": true, "go_live_at": null, "seo_title": "", "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-25T03:59:08.003Z", "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T20:40:48.414Z", "image": 66, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "show_in_menus": false, "numchild": 0, "duration": "00:00:00", "path": "0001000100020005", "place": 8, "slug": "street-art", "content_type": 12, "expire_at": null}	\N	22	1
293	f	2018-01-26 04:21:33.355424+00	{"path": "0001000100030005", "go_live_at": null, "content_type": 6, "depth": 4, "show_in_menus": false, "image": 43, "numchild": 0, "first_published_at": "2017-01-12T20:00:16.547Z", "seo_title": "", "search_description": "", "live": true, "slug": "ngwesaung", "expired": false, "title": "Ngwesaung", "body": "[{\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>You can take a bus from Pathein or Yangon. The roads are better now , so for the about 260km from Yangon it will take about 5 hours, depending what bus you take. There are morning buses (i.e. 6:30am and 7:30am depending on demand, 10000 kyat) that depart from the western Yangon bus terminal (Hlaing Thar Yar Bus Terminal) which is 45 minutes by car taxi from the city centre. There is a bus service (4000 kyat) departing Pathein for Ngwe Saung at 2:00pm again depending on demand, if you miss that hire a moto taxi or jump in a jumbo for 5000 kyat or less (bargain hard!).</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Hiring a car is only worth it if you have missed the morning bus and do not want to ride by night. The difference in time is not big. It will cost around 120$.</p><p><br/></p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"image\\", \\"value\\": {\\"style\\": \\"half\\", \\"image\\": 71, \\"caption\\": \\"Beautiful beach in Ngwe Saung\\"}}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>If you're travelling from Pathein, you can also catch a minivan. It departs from the bus station near Shwezigon Pagoda, the same bus station the local bus leaves from. It's a dark green Toyota Minivan with 'Beach Express' written in red writing on the front and sides. It leaves at 9am and 1pm and charges 3600 Kyat.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p><br/>There is no longer a requirement to remit a copy of your visa and passport prior at a military check point on the way to Ngwe Saung.</p>\\"}, {\\"type\\": \\"paragraph\\", \\"value\\": \\"<p>Passports were handed to the bus operator who did have to show them to guards on the way to Ngwe Saung.</p>\\"}]", "expire_at": null, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "latest_revision_created_at": "2018-01-26T04:20:34.666Z", "owner": 1, "pk": 16, "url_path": "/homepage/places/ngwesaung/", "locked": false}	\N	16	1
